1
00:00:28,737 --> 00:00:35,577
[Wind Howling]

2
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:40,707
[Man Narrating]
This is a simple story...

3
00:00:40,832 --> 00:00:43,502
but not an easy one to tell.

4
00:00:43,585 --> 00:00:45,546
Like a fable, there is sorrow...

5
00:00:45,671 --> 00:00:49,508
and, like a fable,
it is full of wonder and happiness.

6
00:00:53,428 --> 00:00:56,557
I sing what I see. Nothing gets by me.

7
00:00:56,682 --> 00:00:58,392
"Here I am," said I to chaos.

8
00:00:58,517 --> 00:01:01,061
"I am your slave!"
And he: "Good."

9
00:01:01,186 --> 00:01:03,355
"or what?" said I.

10
00:01:03,438 --> 00:01:07,776
Free in the end, I am!
What good is a caress when bliss...

11
00:01:07,901 --> 00:01:09,611
this man came to possess?

12
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:11,613
Here I am, ready.

13
00:01:11,738 --> 00:01:14,575
The trains are gone,
the brakes are gone.

14
00:01:14,616 --> 00:01:18,120
And I can resist no more.
Go, sweet Bacchus, take me.

15
00:01:18,245 --> 00:01:21,290
The brakes are gone!
The brakes are gone!

16
00:01:21,415 --> 00:01:22,749
I heard you.

17
00:01:22,791 --> 00:01:25,043
- No, they're really gone!
- Hit the brakes!

18
00:01:25,127 --> 00:01:27,087
Weren't you reciting a poem?

19
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:31,300
It doesn't work!

20
00:01:31,383 --> 00:01:34,219
[ Both Yelling, Shouting ]

21
00:01:35,554 --> 00:01:37,264
Brake!

22
00:01:37,306 --> 00:01:40,726
We're going to die!
The woods!

23
00:01:46,106 --> 00:01:48,150
Brake!

24
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:54,656
The king is coming!

25
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:57,159
[ Marching Band ]
- There he is!

26
00:01:57,284 --> 00:01:58,785
[ Crowd Cheering ]

27
00:01:58,827 --> 00:02:00,996
It's full of people down there.
Straight.

28
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:02,748
We have no brakes!

29
00:02:02,831 --> 00:02:05,500
We have no brakes! Move!

30
00:02:07,085 --> 00:02:09,171
[ Crowd Cheering, Shouting ]

31
00:02:24,311 --> 00:02:27,272
[ Car Horns Honking ]

32
00:02:27,481 --> 00:02:30,859
[ Music Fades ]

33
00:02:33,779 --> 00:02:36,365
Go for a walk.

34
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:38,700
Otherwise,
we'll get there tomorrow.

35
00:02:38,825 --> 00:02:40,869
I found the screw.

36
00:02:41,995 --> 00:02:43,705
Now what do you need?

37
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:46,833
Nothing.
I need ten minutes alone.

38
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:49,670
All right,
I'll leave you alone.

39
00:02:49,795 --> 00:02:52,047
Do you want the screw
from before?

40
00:02:52,172 --> 00:02:54,383
No, I want to be alone.

41
00:03:05,978 --> 00:03:07,896
Do I toss out the screw
if I find it?

42
00:03:08,021 --> 00:03:11,024
I need ten minutes alone.

43
00:03:11,149 --> 00:03:14,486
I'm washing my hands.

44
00:03:22,077 --> 00:03:25,372
Pretty girl! How's it going?

45
00:03:25,497 --> 00:03:27,165
What are you doing?

46
00:03:27,249 --> 00:03:29,751
Did your mom put this stuff here?

47
00:03:29,877 --> 00:03:31,712
No, the landlady did.

48
00:03:31,753 --> 00:03:34,548
Is it a market? It's beautiful.

49
00:03:34,673 --> 00:03:36,758
How much is it?
How old are you?

50
00:03:38,093 --> 00:03:40,387
- What's your name?
- Eleonora.

51
00:03:40,429 --> 00:03:42,723
Nice to meet you.
I'm Prince Guido.

52
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:46,852
- Prince?
- I'm a prince, I am.

53
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:48,854
All this is mine.

54
00:03:48,937 --> 00:03:51,231
Here starts the prince's principate.

55
00:03:51,273 --> 00:03:53,692
I'll call this place Addis Ababa.

56
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:53,775
I'll change it all.
Out go the cows, in come the camels.

57
00:03:58,655 --> 00:04:00,699
Camels?

58
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:03,035
Even a few hippopotamus.

59
00:04:03,118 --> 00:04:05,245
I must go.
I'm meeting with the princess.

60
00:04:05,370 --> 00:04:07,998
- When?
- Now!

61
00:04:08,081 --> 00:04:09,499
[Woman Yelling]

62
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:14,755
Good morning, Princess!

63
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:18,342
How frightening.
I almost killed myself. Did I hurt you?

64
00:04:18,425 --> 00:04:20,093
I've never been better.

65
00:04:20,177 --> 00:04:21,845
Do you always leave
the house like this?

66
00:04:21,929 --> 00:04:24,765
I wanted to burn that wasps nest,
but I got stung.

67
00:04:24,890 --> 00:04:27,351
A wasp stung you? There?
Allow me.

68
00:04:27,434 --> 00:04:28,769
Hold still, Princess.

69
00:04:28,894 --> 00:04:32,439
A wasp's poison is very dangerous.

70
00:04:32,523 --> 00:04:34,233
You have to get it out.

71
00:04:34,316 --> 00:04:37,736
- Lie down. It'll take a while.
- No, thank you.

72
00:04:40,364 --> 00:04:43,116
- Did you get stung anywhere else?
- No, thank you.

73
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:45,786
What a place here!
It's beautiful!

74
00:04:45,869 --> 00:04:48,872
Pigeons fly, women fall from the sky.
I'm moving here!

75
00:04:48,956 --> 00:04:52,918
It's all his! He wants to fill it
with camels! He's a prince!

76
00:04:53,001 --> 00:04:54,920
Exactly.

77
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:58,215
- Prince Guido at your service, Princess.
[ Car Horn Honking ]

78
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:00,133
I'm coming!

79
00:05:00,217 --> 00:05:02,302
Good-bye, then.

80
00:05:02,386 --> 00:05:05,889
- How can I thank you?
- There's no need.

81
00:05:05,973 --> 00:05:08,100
If you really want
to thank me...

82
00:05:08,183 --> 00:05:11,603
I'll take some eggs to make
a nice omelet for my squire.

83
00:05:11,687 --> 00:05:13,814
Take whatever you want.
It's all yours.

84
00:05:13,897 --> 00:05:15,148
Thank you!

85
00:05:15,274 --> 00:05:19,319
I'll take two-- six.
All right? I'll make a nice omelet.

86
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:22,614
Good-bye, Eleonora!
My regards, Princess.

87
00:05:24,533 --> 00:05:26,743
- Farewell.
[ Car Engine Starting ]

88
00:05:26,827 --> 00:05:30,998
Here I am, Nuvolari!
Tonight's special: omelet!

89
00:05:31,081 --> 00:05:33,125
All camels here!

90
00:05:41,508 --> 00:05:45,679
- Where is this house?
- Turn left. We're almost there.

91
00:05:45,804 --> 00:05:47,848
Is your uncle sleeping with us?

92
00:05:47,973 --> 00:05:51,185
He's lived in the hotel for 30 years.
He's the head maitre.

93
00:05:51,310 --> 00:05:54,354
He's lending us the house.
He uses it for storage.

94
00:05:54,438 --> 00:05:55,689
There. We're here.

95
00:05:56,982 --> 00:05:59,151
That's Robin Hood,
my uncle's horse.

96
00:05:59,234 --> 00:06:01,361
Here's my uncle's buggy
and my uncle's house.

97
00:06:01,445 --> 00:06:03,405
And inside is my uncle.

98
00:06:04,573 --> 00:06:07,201
Hello, dear uncle! Here we are!
Hurry, it's late.

99
00:06:07,326 --> 00:06:09,244
Here we are.
The car broke down!

100
00:06:09,328 --> 00:06:12,122
[ Glass Breaking ]
[ Shouting ]

101
00:06:14,958 --> 00:06:17,044
Uncle!

102
00:06:22,216 --> 00:06:24,384
- Barbarians.
- Who were they?

103
00:06:24,468 --> 00:06:26,720
- Barbarians.
- Why didn't you cry for help?

104
00:06:26,845 --> 00:06:29,556
Silence is
the most powerful cry.

105
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:31,558
Is he your poet friend?

106
00:06:31,642 --> 00:06:34,061
My name is Ferruccio.
I'm also an upholsterer.

107
00:06:35,521 --> 00:06:38,982
Here you are. It's an old storehouse
full of odds and ends.

108
00:06:39,066 --> 00:06:42,569
An old passion--
an odd and end in itself!.

109
00:06:42,694 --> 00:06:45,072
What's all this stuff for?

110
00:06:45,155 --> 00:06:49,409
You can stay as long as you want.
It's not easy to be a waiter.

111
00:06:49,535 --> 00:06:52,746
That's the bed.
Legend has it Garibaldi slept there.

112
00:06:52,871 --> 00:06:54,915
Nothing is more necessary
than the unnecessary.

113
00:06:54,998 --> 00:06:56,375
Barbarians.

114
00:06:56,458 --> 00:07:00,087
The town hall is on Via Sestani,
to the right after the colonnade.

115
00:07:00,212 --> 00:07:03,840
The bathroom, equipped
with the invention of Mr. Bidet.

116
00:07:03,924 --> 00:07:07,845
There are a few books here,
among which The Life of Petrarch.

117
00:07:07,928 --> 00:07:12,933
The kitchen is in there. This is
a velocipede, commonly called a bike.

118
00:07:13,058 --> 00:07:17,271
I have to get back to the hotel.
There's only one key. Don't lose it.

119
00:07:18,105 --> 00:07:22,401
- It's so good to see you.
I'm coming, Robin Hood!
[ Horse Whinnying ]

120
00:07:25,904 --> 00:07:27,447
What an uncle!

121
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:31,243
Look at this!

122
00:07:32,828 --> 00:07:36,874
Didn't I tell you? We're in a city.
You can do whatever you want.

123
00:07:36,957 --> 00:07:39,793
If you want to do something,
you do it.

124
00:07:39,877 --> 00:07:42,421
You want to let yourself go?
You want to yell? Yell!

125
00:07:45,132 --> 00:07:47,050
Stop it!
What are you, crazy?

126
00:07:47,134 --> 00:07:50,095
You can't act
like you do in the country.

127
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:53,807
You've been yelling like a madman.
You can't yell!

128
00:07:53,932 --> 00:07:55,767
Mary! The key!

129
00:07:55,851 --> 00:07:58,645
[Key Bouncing On Ground]

130
00:07:59,813 --> 00:08:01,773
See? You can't yell.

131
00:08:01,899 --> 00:08:05,652
Understand? If you stopped thinking
so much about poetry...

132
00:08:05,777 --> 00:08:09,656
you'd make your father happier
and you'd make more money than him.

133
00:08:09,781 --> 00:08:11,909
That's right, Oreste.
That's what I tell him too.

134
00:08:11,992 --> 00:08:14,244
You have to settle down!

135
00:08:14,328 --> 00:08:17,080
What a nice hat.
How does it look?

136
00:08:17,164 --> 00:08:19,833
- Nice. How does it look?
- Nice, but it's mine.

137
00:08:19,917 --> 00:08:22,002
When do I start working?

138
00:08:22,127 --> 00:08:24,463
You're already late.
Right away!

139
00:08:24,546 --> 00:08:27,257
Get that armchair
and take it to the workshop.

140
00:08:27,341 --> 00:08:31,595
- That one?
- That one. And be careful!

141
00:08:31,678 --> 00:08:34,598
Good. I'm going to the town hall.
Good-bye.

142
00:08:34,681 --> 00:08:37,518
Good-bye,
and behave yourselves...

143
00:08:37,643 --> 00:08:40,187
because these are hard times.

144
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:41,980
Hard, hard times!

145
00:08:42,064 --> 00:08:44,024
They're hard times?

146
00:08:44,107 --> 00:08:47,194
Why, what are your
political views?

147
00:08:47,277 --> 00:08:50,531
Benito! Adolph!
Be good!

148
00:08:50,614 --> 00:08:52,533
What did you say?

149
00:08:53,825 --> 00:08:56,870
I said, how are things going?

150
00:08:56,995 --> 00:08:58,997
Good-bye, then.

151
00:08:59,081 --> 00:09:00,707
Careful!
You'll break the legs!

152
00:09:02,417 --> 00:09:03,627
Good-bye!

153
00:09:09,591 --> 00:09:14,137
He pulled it off.
He took my hat. I'll find him though.

154
00:09:14,221 --> 00:09:16,557
Benito,
you're going to get a slap!

155
00:09:18,559 --> 00:09:22,521
I need to do the whole bureaucratic
procedure to open a bookstore.

156
00:09:22,604 --> 00:09:25,023
- Does it take a long time?
- Years.

157
00:09:25,107 --> 00:09:27,025
Then we'd better
open a file now.

158
00:09:27,109 --> 00:09:30,737
First you apply, and
the department head has to sign it.

159
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:37,369
I almost scrambled my eggs.
I've had them since yesterday.

160
00:09:37,452 --> 00:09:40,539
I forgot about them.
Thank God they didn't break. Take note.

161
00:09:40,622 --> 00:09:42,416
I, the undersigned,
Guido Orefice...

162
00:09:42,541 --> 00:09:45,419
- am applying to open--
- He can't sign it now!

163
00:09:46,628 --> 00:09:48,714
What's going on?

164
00:09:48,797 --> 00:09:51,341
I need your signature
to open a bookstore.

165
00:09:51,425 --> 00:09:54,511
- Miss, what's going on?
- Mr. Rodolfo, I told him.

166
00:09:54,595 --> 00:09:57,055
-Just one signature.
- No, I can't.

167
00:09:57,180 --> 00:09:59,725
My substitute will be here
in an hour. Ask him.

168
00:09:59,808 --> 00:10:03,520
- All I need is a signature.
- We close at one here!

169
00:10:03,604 --> 00:10:05,689
It's ten to one.

170
00:10:05,772 --> 00:10:07,232
File a complaint.

171
00:10:08,567 --> 00:10:11,528
Boy, is he nasty.

172
00:10:11,612 --> 00:10:15,240
To sign a paper, open a file,
all he had to do was--

173
00:10:15,324 --> 00:10:18,452
Now I have to wait one hour
for his substitute.

174
00:10:18,535 --> 00:10:21,038
I'm filing a complaint.
Write, "I, the undersigned--"

175
00:10:22,331 --> 00:10:24,291
[ Groaning ]

176
00:10:24,458 --> 00:10:26,376
What a wallop!

177
00:10:29,713 --> 00:10:32,466
Are you hurt?
I'll help you.

178
00:10:32,591 --> 00:10:34,301
Come here.
I didn't do it on purpose.

179
00:10:34,384 --> 00:10:35,969
Don't touch me!

180
00:10:37,304 --> 00:10:40,307
You can forget
about your bookshop!

181
00:10:41,391 --> 00:10:42,643
No, the eggs!

182
00:10:45,521 --> 00:10:47,898
You scoundrel!
I'll kill you!

183
00:10:53,403 --> 00:10:55,614
[ Bell Ringing ]

184
00:10:57,074 --> 00:10:58,742
Out of the way!

185
00:11:00,035 --> 00:11:02,454
[ Screams ]
[ All Laughing ]

186
00:11:05,624 --> 00:11:08,126
Good morning, Princess.

187
00:11:09,294 --> 00:11:12,464
I wonder if we'll ever bump
into each other standing up.

188
00:11:12,589 --> 00:11:15,300
Excuse me,
but I've got to run.

189
00:11:15,425 --> 00:11:18,053
Farewell, Princess!

190
00:11:31,483 --> 00:11:34,069
- Chicken.
- That's easy.

191
00:11:34,111 --> 00:11:36,947
It's served whole,
bottom down on the plate.

192
00:11:37,072 --> 00:11:38,949
"Will you cut it for me?"
" Naturally."

193
00:11:38,991 --> 00:11:42,619
I stick the blade under the wing,
then I rip off the drumstick.

194
00:11:42,744 --> 00:11:45,497
I cut the meat along
the bottom of the breastbone.

195
00:11:45,622 --> 00:11:48,292
- Off go the wings, breast and skin.
- Lobster.

196
00:11:48,417 --> 00:11:50,836
Piece of cake, Uncle.

197
00:11:50,961 --> 00:11:54,006
I stick the wing under the leg.

198
00:11:54,131 --> 00:11:56,592
Off goes the leg.
I rip off the lobster, stick the--

199
00:11:56,675 --> 00:11:58,927
Lobster is a crustacean.

200
00:12:00,971 --> 00:12:04,433
Off goes the crust...
of the crustacean.

201
00:12:04,516 --> 00:12:09,771
Off go the crust and antennae.
Who eats the antennae?

202
00:12:09,813 --> 00:12:12,691
Off go the antennae,
off goes the lobster.

203
00:12:12,816 --> 00:12:14,318
There's nothing left.

204
00:12:14,443 --> 00:12:17,321
We're out of lobster,
but the chicken is delicious.

205
00:12:18,614 --> 00:12:22,868
- I don't remember how to do lobster.
- You serve it as is.

206
00:12:22,993 --> 00:12:25,037
There's no need to touch it!

207
00:12:25,162 --> 00:12:27,497
That's too easy.
That's why I didn't remember.

208
00:12:27,539 --> 00:12:29,333
- Continue.
- Behavior!

209
00:12:29,458 --> 00:12:31,543
Stand by.
Still, like this.

210
00:12:31,668 --> 00:12:33,503
"Waiter?"
"Yes?"

211
00:12:33,545 --> 00:12:36,006
In position.
Stand by behavior. Waiter!

212
00:12:36,215 --> 00:12:39,801
[ Continues In Italian ]

213
00:12:44,389 --> 00:12:47,017
Why only me?
There must be other waiters, right?

214
00:12:49,186 --> 00:12:51,355
Bowing!
Piece of cake.

215
00:12:53,524 --> 00:12:56,360
You bow down, further.

216
00:12:56,401 --> 00:13:00,405
Like this, at a 45 degree angle,
just like a champagne bottle.

217
00:13:00,531 --> 00:13:03,534
45 degrees, even 50, 55.

218
00:13:03,659 --> 00:13:06,578
90 degrees.
A right angle. 1 80.

219
00:13:06,703 --> 00:13:10,082
How far do I bow down?
1 80 degrees? Like this?

220
00:13:10,207 --> 00:13:13,168
Think of a sunflower.
They bow to the sun.

221
00:13:13,252 --> 00:13:15,837
But if you see some
that are too bowed down...

222
00:13:15,921 --> 00:13:17,548
it means they're dead!

223
00:13:17,673 --> 00:13:20,050
You're serving.
You're not a servant.

224
00:13:20,175 --> 00:13:22,344
Serving is a supreme art.

225
00:13:22,427 --> 00:13:24,930
God is the first servant.

226
00:13:25,055 --> 00:13:28,225
God serves men,
but he's not a servant to men.

227
00:13:28,350 --> 00:13:32,437
- There was no button here.
- It doesn't go there, silly.

228
00:13:32,604 --> 00:13:35,858
I have to take the car back to Pop.
He's counting on it.

229
00:13:35,899 --> 00:13:37,943
You'll take it back
in a month or so.

230
00:13:38,068 --> 00:13:40,946
No, I've got to get it back soon.
You know why?

231
00:13:42,239 --> 00:13:43,782
Why?

232
00:13:47,744 --> 00:13:50,080
Ferruccio? Ferruccio?

233
00:13:50,455 --> 00:13:53,876
- What? What time is it?
- Were you sleeping?

234
00:13:53,917 --> 00:13:56,295
Of course I was.

235
00:13:56,420 --> 00:13:59,256
You fell asleep
while talking to me!

236
00:13:59,381 --> 00:14:01,758
- How did you do that?
- Schopenhauer.

237
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:03,594
Who?

238
00:14:03,719 --> 00:14:07,306
Schopenhauer says that with willpower,
you can do anything.

239
00:14:07,431 --> 00:14:09,308
"I am what I want to be."

240
00:14:09,433 --> 00:14:12,561
Right now I want to sleep,
so I was saying to myself...

241
00:14:12,644 --> 00:14:14,938
"I'm sleeping, sleeping,"
and I fell asleep.

242
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:18,317
Amazing.
And it's simple too.

243
00:14:18,442 --> 00:14:21,653
I want to try too.
I'm sleeping, sleeping, sleeping--

244
00:14:21,778 --> 00:14:24,114
[ Continues ]

245
00:14:24,239 --> 00:14:26,909
Don't move your hands.
You're not a juggler.

246
00:14:26,950 --> 00:14:30,412
It's a matter of thought.
It's serious, and it takes time.

247
00:14:30,454 --> 00:14:32,456
We'll talk about it tomorrow.

248
00:14:33,457 --> 00:14:35,334
Amazing, though.

249
00:14:37,002 --> 00:14:38,795
Wake up.

250
00:14:38,921 --> 00:14:41,506
Wake up.

251
00:14:43,634 --> 00:14:45,510
What is it now?
What are you doing?

252
00:14:45,636 --> 00:14:47,846
- It totally works!
- What works?

253
00:14:47,971 --> 00:14:51,975
Schopenhauer.
You know what I just said? "Wake up."

254
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:55,437
Bam, you woke up.
This theory is incredible.

255
00:14:55,479 --> 00:14:57,981
- How does it work?
- You were yelling in my ear!

256
00:14:58,106 --> 00:15:00,943
That's why I woke up.

257
00:15:00,984 --> 00:15:04,363
- So I should say it quieter.
- Don't say it at all!

258
00:15:08,033 --> 00:15:10,160
It's deep.
You have to think it.

259
00:15:14,623 --> 00:15:16,667
Why are you running?
Slow down!

260
00:15:16,792 --> 00:15:18,293
Hurry up. It's late!

261
00:15:18,335 --> 00:15:22,548
- Mary, the key!
[ Key Bouncing On Ground ]

262
00:15:22,714 --> 00:15:24,550
Every morning,
she throws the key.

263
00:15:24,675 --> 00:15:26,009
Look!

264
00:15:26,134 --> 00:15:28,971
There's that teacher.
Boy, is she pretty.

265
00:15:29,012 --> 00:15:32,349
I even dreamt about her.
Come with me. I'll introduce you.

266
00:15:32,474 --> 00:15:35,519
- Holy smokes! Stay still!
- What is it?

267
00:15:35,644 --> 00:15:37,020
Don't move!

268
00:15:37,062 --> 00:15:41,233
The one in the car.
He's that jerk the eggs fell on.

269
00:15:41,358 --> 00:15:43,652
He'll kill me if he sees me.
Be good.

270
00:15:43,694 --> 00:15:45,904
- What's he doing?
- He's talking.

271
00:15:46,029 --> 00:15:48,073
- What's he saying?
- How do I know?

272
00:15:48,198 --> 00:15:51,702
- What's he doing?
- He's saying good-bye.

273
00:15:51,827 --> 00:15:55,330
He's got a car just like mine!
There he is!

274
00:15:55,372 --> 00:15:58,250
Don't move.
He'll kill me if he sees me!

275
00:15:58,375 --> 00:15:59,835
Stay still, Ferruccio.

276
00:16:03,505 --> 00:16:06,008
Good morning, Princess!

277
00:16:07,718 --> 00:16:10,929
It's you again.
How do you do this?

278
00:16:11,054 --> 00:16:14,683
This is the princess
who fell from the sky into my arms.

279
00:16:14,725 --> 00:16:18,061
Is he the one who sucked
the stinger out of your thigh?

280
00:16:18,103 --> 00:16:21,231
Yes. We keep meeting like this.
You just suddenly show up.

281
00:16:21,356 --> 00:16:24,693
We could make plans to meet.

282
00:16:24,735 --> 00:16:27,279
- Tonight at 8:00?
- No, it's nicer this way.

283
00:16:27,404 --> 00:16:29,031
Let's go, Dora.
You'll be late.

284
00:16:31,408 --> 00:16:33,911
I hope we meet again
suddenly.

285
00:16:34,036 --> 00:16:37,206
Farewell, Princess!

286
00:16:37,289 --> 00:16:39,458
Did you see her?
She's pretty, huh?

287
00:16:39,583 --> 00:16:41,919
She likes it
when I suddenly appear.

288
00:16:50,052 --> 00:16:52,471
I don't believe it.

289
00:16:52,596 --> 00:16:54,973
"Obscurity."

290
00:16:55,098 --> 00:16:56,725
You're a genius!

291
00:16:56,808 --> 00:16:59,811
"The bigger it is,
the less you see it."

292
00:16:59,937 --> 00:17:01,605
Solution: obscurity.

293
00:17:01,730 --> 00:17:04,399
Marvelous.
Did you make that riddle up?

294
00:17:04,483 --> 00:17:09,154
No, but you solved it in five minutes.
It took me eight days.

295
00:17:09,279 --> 00:17:10,906
Obscurity!

296
00:17:10,989 --> 00:17:13,784
Salmon, salad
and a glass of white wine.

297
00:17:13,909 --> 00:17:16,078
Listen to this one, Guido.

298
00:17:17,120 --> 00:17:20,249
If I may, it's my turn.

299
00:17:20,290 --> 00:17:22,417
My pop told me this
when I was a wee boy.

300
00:17:22,459 --> 00:17:25,087
"The dwarves and Snow White
sit down for a bite.

301
00:17:25,170 --> 00:17:29,675
How fast can you guess
what she serves her guests next?"

302
00:17:33,095 --> 00:17:35,347
It sounds refined.

303
00:17:35,472 --> 00:17:37,599
I want to solve it right now.

304
00:17:37,641 --> 00:17:41,019
- Eat first or it'll get cold.
- I don't want to. It's too late.

305
00:17:41,144 --> 00:17:43,272
Salad, salmon, white wine.
It's light.

306
00:17:43,355 --> 00:17:45,315
The dwarves...

307
00:17:46,650 --> 00:17:48,360
and Snow White.

308
00:17:49,319 --> 00:17:51,321
- Guido?
- Si?

309
00:17:51,864 --> 00:17:54,867
- Is the kitchen closed?
- Everybody's gone. Why?

310
00:17:54,992 --> 00:17:58,120
A gentleman from Rome is here
from the Ministry. He wants to eat.

311
00:17:58,161 --> 00:17:59,788
The kitchen is closed.

312
00:17:59,872 --> 00:18:02,374
Oh, well, he would have
given you a good tip.

313
00:18:02,499 --> 00:18:04,376
The kitchen is open.

314
00:18:05,168 --> 00:18:06,712
Come right in.

315
00:18:09,339 --> 00:18:11,300
- Prego.
- Grazie.

316
00:18:15,846 --> 00:18:18,181
Doctor, you're not eating anything?

317
00:18:20,851 --> 00:18:22,477
- "The dwarves and Snow White--"
- Buonasera.

318
00:18:24,521 --> 00:18:28,150
I know the kitchen is closed.
Maybe a cold dish.

319
00:18:28,191 --> 00:18:32,905
- It's all delicious. Take your pick.
- Something light.

320
00:18:33,030 --> 00:18:35,908
Well, we've got meat,
a nice heavy steak...

321
00:18:36,033 --> 00:18:39,369
Iamb, kidneys,
some greasy breaded liver.

322
00:18:39,494 --> 00:18:41,914
- Otherwise, there's fish.
- Fish.

323
00:18:42,039 --> 00:18:45,375
We have...
a nice fatty turbot...

324
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:48,712
eel stuffed with fatty sausage
and greased with Grand Marnier...

325
00:18:48,837 --> 00:18:50,547
or some lean salmon--

326
00:18:50,672 --> 00:18:53,050
The salmon, thank you.

327
00:18:53,091 --> 00:18:55,677
- Side dish?
- There's a side dish too?

328
00:18:57,054 --> 00:18:59,890
Of course.
We have very, very fried mushrooms...

329
00:18:59,932 --> 00:19:03,602
buttered potatoes in Nancy butter
with a flaky sauce--

330
00:19:03,727 --> 00:19:08,565
Is there a small, light salad?
If not, nothing.

331
00:19:08,607 --> 00:19:13,445
A light salad? What a pity.
The very, very fried mushrooms...

332
00:19:13,570 --> 00:19:16,198
were out of this world.
So, a light salad...

333
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:18,742
a lean salmon
and a glass of white wine.

334
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:21,119
Perfect.
As soon as possible.

335
00:19:21,245 --> 00:19:23,121
I'll do my best.

336
00:19:30,128 --> 00:19:32,047
Prego.

337
00:19:39,429 --> 00:19:42,015
" How fast can you guess
what she serves her guests next?"

338
00:19:42,099 --> 00:19:43,392
Right.

339
00:19:44,851 --> 00:19:47,521
- "The dwarves and Snow White."
- Good night, Doctor.

340
00:19:47,604 --> 00:19:49,773
Good night, genius.

341
00:19:51,733 --> 00:19:55,612
What did he say? The dwarves?
What is he, drunk?

342
00:19:55,696 --> 00:19:57,447
It's a riddle.
"Seven seconds."

343
00:20:00,117 --> 00:20:03,287
"Seven seconds" is the solution.
"The dwarves and Snow White."

344
00:20:03,370 --> 00:20:05,622
If there are seven dwarves dining...

345
00:20:05,706 --> 00:20:08,083
and she serves seconds,
that means "seven seconds."

346
00:20:09,543 --> 00:20:12,963
Doctor Lessing is a physician,
a very serious person.

347
00:20:13,046 --> 00:20:16,300
But he's obsessed with riddles.
He loses sleep over them.

348
00:20:19,386 --> 00:20:21,889
Excuse me.
The " Francesco Petrarca" school.

349
00:20:23,557 --> 00:20:26,894
The elementary school? A friend
of mine teaches there. It's beautiful.

350
00:20:26,977 --> 00:20:29,313
It's not far from here. Why?

351
00:20:29,396 --> 00:20:31,899
Good. I can sleep
an extra half-hour.

352
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:35,402
Do you have to go
to that school tomorrow morning?

353
00:20:35,485 --> 00:20:37,237
They're expecting me at 8:30.

354
00:20:44,161 --> 00:20:46,997
Please, children, silence!
A moment of attention.

355
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:50,167
The inspector from Rome
will be here shortly.

356
00:20:50,250 --> 00:20:52,377
I want to make
a good impression on him.

357
00:20:52,461 --> 00:20:56,131
Listen very quietly
and carefully to what he says.

358
00:20:56,256 --> 00:20:59,468
He'll tell us some very important
things about our beautiful country.

359
00:21:00,761 --> 00:21:03,263
The inspector is here, ma'am.

360
00:21:03,347 --> 00:21:06,016
He's already here?
He's early!

361
00:21:06,099 --> 00:21:07,726
Sit down, Roberto!

362
00:21:07,809 --> 00:21:12,022
[ Footsteps Approaching ]
[ Woman Claps ]

363
00:21:12,272 --> 00:21:14,775
All rise!

364
00:21:18,946 --> 00:21:20,948
Good morning, Princess.

365
00:21:23,951 --> 00:21:27,538
Good morning, Mr. Inspector.
I'm the principal.

366
00:21:27,621 --> 00:21:29,873
These are some of our teachers.

367
00:21:32,459 --> 00:21:33,877
Good.

368
00:21:36,129 --> 00:21:37,548
Therefore--
[ Mumbling ]

369
00:21:39,633 --> 00:21:43,095
How many years have you taught
in this school district?

370
00:21:43,178 --> 00:21:44,638
Sixteen.

371
00:21:46,807 --> 00:21:49,726
Are you up to date
with the ongoing...

372
00:21:49,810 --> 00:21:51,979
school program approved
by the Ministry this year?

373
00:21:52,062 --> 00:21:53,480
Yes.

374
00:21:55,357 --> 00:21:59,653
Did you read the bulletin
regarding childhood hygiene?

375
00:21:59,695 --> 00:22:01,655
Of course.

376
00:22:03,824 --> 00:22:06,201
What are you doing on Sunday?

377
00:22:06,326 --> 00:22:11,081
No, I mean, Sunday is St. Mary's Day.
What are you doing?

378
00:22:11,164 --> 00:22:13,542
I'm going to the theater.

379
00:22:15,544 --> 00:22:17,921
- To see what?
- Offenbach.

380
00:22:18,005 --> 00:22:20,090
Right,
they're playing Offenbach.

381
00:22:23,677 --> 00:22:25,554
Fine. Well--

382
00:22:26,555 --> 00:22:29,516
Thank you very much, and good-bye.
I just came to--

383
00:22:29,558 --> 00:22:31,059
We know.

384
00:22:31,184 --> 00:22:33,437
As you know, the inspector...

385
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:36,356
came from Rome to talk to us
about the race manifesto...

386
00:22:36,398 --> 00:22:39,860
signed by the most well versed
Italian scientists.

387
00:22:39,902 --> 00:22:43,113
He will, and we're very honored...

388
00:22:43,196 --> 00:22:45,699
demonstrate to us that our race...

389
00:22:45,741 --> 00:22:47,701
is a superior race--

390
00:22:47,743 --> 00:22:49,953
the best of all.

391
00:22:50,037 --> 00:22:51,872
Take your seats.

392
00:22:53,707 --> 00:22:56,335
Go ahead, Inspector.

393
00:22:56,418 --> 00:22:59,129
- Our race--
- Is superior.

394
00:22:59,213 --> 00:23:00,631
Naturally!

395
00:23:01,882 --> 00:23:03,967
Our race is superior.

396
00:23:04,051 --> 00:23:07,638
I've just come from Rome,
right this minute...

397
00:23:07,721 --> 00:23:11,058
to come and tell you in order
that you'll know, children...

398
00:23:11,141 --> 00:23:13,060
that our race
is a superior one.

399
00:23:13,143 --> 00:23:15,062
I was...

400
00:23:15,103 --> 00:23:19,316
chosen, I was,
by racist Italian scientists...

401
00:23:19,399 --> 00:23:21,318
in order to demonstrate...

402
00:23:21,401 --> 00:23:24,071
how superior our race is.

403
00:23:24,154 --> 00:23:27,908
Why did they pick me, children?

404
00:23:29,743 --> 00:23:32,079
Must I tell you?

405
00:23:34,790 --> 00:23:36,750
Where can you find...

406
00:23:36,792 --> 00:23:39,962
someone more handsome than me?

407
00:23:40,087 --> 00:23:43,966
Justly so, there is silence.
I'm an original "superior race"...

408
00:23:44,091 --> 00:23:45,467
pure Aryan.

409
00:23:45,592 --> 00:23:47,344
Children.

410
00:23:47,427 --> 00:23:50,430
Let's start with something that
one says: "What's so big about that?"

411
00:23:50,514 --> 00:23:55,018
The ear. Look at
the perfection of this ear.

412
00:23:55,102 --> 00:23:57,646
Left auricle...

413
00:23:57,771 --> 00:24:00,315
with a pendant
little bell at the end.

414
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:03,318
Check it out.
Movable cartilage.

415
00:24:03,443 --> 00:24:05,028
Bendable.

416
00:24:05,112 --> 00:24:07,990
Find two ears more beautiful
than these and I'll leave!

417
00:24:08,115 --> 00:24:11,952
But you have to show me them.
They dream about these in France!

418
00:24:12,035 --> 00:24:15,038
Races exist, children.
You bet they do!

419
00:24:15,122 --> 00:24:18,292
But let's continue.
I want to show you something else.

420
00:24:18,375 --> 00:24:20,085
Pay attention.

421
00:24:21,336 --> 00:24:23,463
He said Inspector?

422
00:24:23,547 --> 00:24:25,507
From Rome?

423
00:24:26,967 --> 00:24:31,054
- The belly button!
[ Laughing ]

424
00:24:31,138 --> 00:24:34,349
Take a look at this belly button!
What a knot!

425
00:24:34,474 --> 00:24:36,727
But you can't untie it,
not even with your teeth!

426
00:24:36,810 --> 00:24:39,730
Those racist scientists tried it.
Not a chance!

427
00:24:39,813 --> 00:24:42,816
This is an Italian belly button.
It's part of our race!

428
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:44,943
Check out this style!

429
00:24:45,027 --> 00:24:49,865
Look at these muscles:
ceps, biceps, triceps!

430
00:24:49,990 --> 00:24:52,910
Look at this beauty!
Admire this hip!

431
00:24:54,536 --> 00:24:56,914
[ Humming ]

432
00:24:57,414 --> 00:25:00,250
Just look at the movement!

433
00:25:00,334 --> 00:25:01,543
Gentlemen!

434
00:25:04,004 --> 00:25:05,964
I must say good-bye now.

435
00:25:06,048 --> 00:25:09,092
I have to go.
I have an appointment.

436
00:25:09,176 --> 00:25:11,887
I'll make my Aryan exit
and bid you farewell.

437
00:25:12,012 --> 00:25:13,847
Farewell!
The belly button!

438
00:25:13,889 --> 00:25:16,183
[ Laughter Continues ]

439
00:25:16,350 --> 00:25:19,186
I'll see you in Venice, Princess.

440
00:25:20,687 --> 00:25:23,440
[ Classical ]

441
00:25:43,418 --> 00:25:46,380
[ Opera In French ]

442
00:26:22,249 --> 00:26:24,251
I can only hear
out of this ear.

443
00:26:42,811 --> 00:26:45,981
Look at me, Princess.

444
00:26:46,106 --> 00:26:47,983
Go on, I'm down here.

445
00:26:49,943 --> 00:26:52,654
Look at me, Princess.

446
00:27:08,629 --> 00:27:11,340
Turn around, Princess.

447
00:27:12,633 --> 00:27:15,135
Turn around, around--

448
00:27:15,219 --> 00:27:17,137
[ Continues In Italian ]

449
00:27:52,297 --> 00:27:55,676
- Can we get a chocolate ice cream?
- Yes, but we'll have to be quick.

450
00:27:55,801 --> 00:27:56,969
Why?

451
00:27:57,052 --> 00:28:01,265
We have to be at the Prefect's at eight.
We were invited to dinner.

452
00:28:01,348 --> 00:28:03,141
- Where?
- At the Prefect's.

453
00:28:04,351 --> 00:28:07,104
Have pity on me, Lord.
Let it not be true.

454
00:28:07,187 --> 00:28:10,315
- Another dinner at the Prefect's?
- Your mother is coming too.

455
00:28:10,399 --> 00:28:11,817
Bingo!

456
00:28:11,900 --> 00:28:16,572
Let's us just go to dinner.
We'll stop by the Prefect's for coffee.

457
00:28:16,655 --> 00:28:18,740
I'm not coming!

458
00:28:18,824 --> 00:28:21,410
All right, I heard you!
I'll tell him we're not going.

459
00:28:21,493 --> 00:28:23,745
It'll just be me and you.

460
00:28:24,997 --> 00:28:28,208
- Good evening, Rodolfo!
- Good evening, Mr. Prefect.

461
00:28:29,418 --> 00:28:32,045
I'll see you later at my house.
I'll expect you at 8:00.

462
00:28:32,170 --> 00:28:34,047
We'll be there at 8:00 sharp.

463
00:28:36,341 --> 00:28:38,260
[ Groans ]

464
00:28:38,427 --> 00:28:40,762
Where is she?
Did you see her?

465
00:28:40,846 --> 00:28:43,223
- She has to be here.
- You're here?

466
00:28:44,850 --> 00:28:47,436
On time tomorrow, got it?

467
00:28:47,519 --> 00:28:49,938
Did you take that stuff
out of the car?

468
00:28:50,022 --> 00:28:52,649
It's silk. Don't ruin it.
Be very careful.

469
00:28:54,443 --> 00:28:56,945
- What an opera.
- Beautiful!

470
00:28:59,448 --> 00:29:02,284
Is that one of your curtains?

471
00:29:02,367 --> 00:29:05,454
No, it must be
one of my colleague's.

472
00:29:08,040 --> 00:29:10,042
He took my hat again!

473
00:29:11,043 --> 00:29:13,337
- Let's go.
- Don't you see how it's raining?

474
00:29:13,420 --> 00:29:16,131
- You go get the car.
- It's right around the corner.

475
00:29:16,215 --> 00:29:18,592
All right, you wait here.

476
00:29:18,717 --> 00:29:22,054
- I'll pull up right here and toot.
[ Thunderclap ]

477
00:29:23,138 --> 00:29:25,390
Give me the key!

478
00:29:25,474 --> 00:29:27,643
Not the house key!
The car key!

479
00:29:29,228 --> 00:29:31,396
The car key?
Are you crazy?

480
00:29:31,480 --> 00:29:34,149
Keep him busy, you know,
the jerk the eggs fell on.

481
00:29:34,233 --> 00:29:36,735
Keep him busy as long as you can.
I'll see you tonight.

482
00:29:36,818 --> 00:29:39,029
Inside the car there's--
Go slow!

483
00:29:45,327 --> 00:29:48,121
[ Horn Honking ]

484
00:29:56,255 --> 00:29:58,632
The least you could have done
is come get me with the umbrella.

485
00:29:58,757 --> 00:30:01,635
You're just plain rude.
Look what a mess I am.

486
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:05,764
Plus, dinner at the Prefect's
gets me so nervous!

487
00:30:05,847 --> 00:30:09,685
[ Hiccupping ]
I knew it. I've got the hiccups.

488
00:30:09,768 --> 00:30:13,939
I always get them when I'm made
to do something I don't want to.

489
00:30:14,022 --> 00:30:17,109
Don't you know that it takes
so little to make me happy?

490
00:30:17,192 --> 00:30:19,945
A chocolate ice cream is enough!
Even two!

491
00:30:20,028 --> 00:30:23,532
A nice walk together
and then whatever happens happens.

492
00:30:23,615 --> 00:30:25,867
Instead you--
[ Yells ]

493
00:30:26,952 --> 00:30:28,870
