00:47:59,796 --> 00:48:03,050
He's got the keys to the house,
darn it all!

742
00:48:08,138 --> 00:48:11,183
Some wire.
I can open it if I find some wire.

743
00:48:12,309 --> 00:48:15,646
I'm a whiz with wire.
My pop taught me.

744
00:48:15,729 --> 00:48:19,107
I used to make toys out of wire
when I was a kid.

745
00:48:24,029 --> 00:48:26,114
[ Grunting ]

746
00:48:26,615 --> 00:48:28,450
I opened it.

747
00:48:53,183 --> 00:48:56,103
[ Birds Twittering ]

748
00:48:56,478 --> 00:48:57,896
Joshua!

749
00:49:00,315 --> 00:49:02,734
Let's go. You're going
to make Mommy late.

750
00:49:07,322 --> 00:49:09,575
I lost my tank.

751
00:49:09,658 --> 00:49:12,035
Don't worry.
We'll find it.

752
00:49:12,119 --> 00:49:14,705
Where did you leave the tank?

753
00:49:14,788 --> 00:49:17,124
- It's on the stairs.
- I'll get it.

754
00:49:17,207 --> 00:49:19,835
Hold the bicycle.
I'll get it.

755
00:49:22,921 --> 00:49:24,339
Here.

756
00:49:25,424 --> 00:49:26,758
Let's go.

757
00:49:27,843 --> 00:49:30,887
- Go, Pop!
- Go slow!

758
00:49:30,971 --> 00:49:33,724
You're late for school! Go!

759
00:49:33,807 --> 00:49:36,393
- There's a horse! Two horses!
[ Bicycle Bell Ringing ]

760
00:49:39,187 --> 00:49:41,481
Stop ringing that bell!
It's driving me mad!

761
00:49:41,565 --> 00:49:45,152
- It's not me, it's Joshua.
- It's not me, it's Pop!

762
00:49:45,235 --> 00:49:47,154
Stop it! Let me off!.

763
00:49:57,372 --> 00:49:58,999
Here we are.

764
00:49:59,082 --> 00:50:00,709
See you tonight.

765
00:50:02,169 --> 00:50:04,296
Ciao, Dora. Ciao.

766
00:50:04,546 --> 00:50:06,548
Go fast, Pop!

767
00:50:06,715 --> 00:50:09,217
Uno, due, tre!

768
00:50:11,053 --> 00:50:14,848
[ Whistle Blowing ]
[ Man Shouting Commands In German ]

769
00:50:17,851 --> 00:50:19,770
Can we buy this for Mommy?

770
00:50:19,853 --> 00:50:22,898
- How much does it cost?
- Fifteen lire.

771
00:50:22,981 --> 00:50:26,401
It's a fake. It's probably
a fake cake, like your tank.

772
00:50:26,485 --> 00:50:28,153
Let's go, Joshua.

773
00:50:28,236 --> 00:50:30,614
"No Jews or dogs...

774
00:50:30,697 --> 00:50:33,575
allowed."

775
00:50:35,285 --> 00:50:39,623
Why aren't Jews or dogs
allowed to go in?

776
00:50:39,706 --> 00:50:42,167
They just don't want
Jews or dogs to go in.

777
00:50:42,251 --> 00:50:44,503
Everybody does what they want to.

778
00:50:44,586 --> 00:50:46,672
There's a hardware store there.

779
00:50:46,755 --> 00:50:49,716
They don't let Spanish people
or horses into his store.

780
00:50:49,800 --> 00:50:51,718
Further ahead, there's a drugstore.

781
00:50:51,802 --> 00:50:55,222
I was with a Chinese friend of mine
yesterday who had a kangaroo.

782
00:50:55,305 --> 00:50:58,475
I said, "May we?" " No, we don't want
any Chinese or kangaroos here."

783
00:50:58,558 --> 00:51:00,686
They don't like them.
What can I tell you?

784
00:51:00,769 --> 00:51:03,438
We let everybody
into our bookshop.

785
00:51:03,522 --> 00:51:05,440
No. From now on,
we'll write it too.

786
00:51:05,524 --> 00:51:08,026
- Is there anybody you don't like?
- Spiders. What about you?

787
00:51:08,110 --> 00:51:10,612
I don't like Visigoths.
Starting tomorrow we'll write...

788
00:51:10,696 --> 00:51:13,615
" No spiders and Visigoths allowed."

789
00:51:13,699 --> 00:51:16,660
I'm sick and tired
of these Visigoths.

790
00:51:16,827 --> 00:51:18,537
[ Humming ]

791
00:51:25,252 --> 00:51:26,670
Good morning.

792
00:51:26,753 --> 00:51:28,922
Everything's half price.

793
00:51:29,006 --> 00:51:32,217
- Guido Orefice?
- That's me.

794
00:51:32,301 --> 00:51:35,887
- You have to come to the Prefect's.
- Again?

795
00:51:35,971 --> 00:51:38,015
- He already went.
- Let's go.

796
00:51:38,098 --> 00:51:39,141
Why?

797
00:51:42,311 --> 00:51:44,896
- Is that man with you?
- Yes. Let's go.

798
00:51:44,980 --> 00:51:46,356
All right.

799
00:51:46,440 --> 00:51:48,191
- I'm coming too.
- No.

800
00:51:48,275 --> 00:51:50,694
You stay here.
It won't take long, will it?

801
00:51:50,777 --> 00:51:52,696
Not long at all.

802
00:51:53,614 --> 00:51:56,283
Joshua, make sure
you treat the customers good!

803
00:51:56,366 --> 00:51:59,119
I'll be right back.

804
00:51:59,202 --> 00:52:01,038
Buongiorno.

805
00:52:30,442 --> 00:52:32,611
- Buongiorno.
- Buongiorno.

806
00:53:01,348 --> 00:53:04,559
- I'll take this one.
- It costs five lire.

807
00:53:04,643 --> 00:53:08,313
No, it says ten lire.

808
00:53:08,397 --> 00:53:11,191
Everything's half price.

809
00:53:13,402 --> 00:53:17,739
Give this to your mom
and tell her it's from Grandma.

810
00:53:17,823 --> 00:53:21,410
I've never seen
my grandma before.

811
00:53:21,493 --> 00:53:24,162
- Would you like to meet her?
- Yes.

812
00:53:25,414 --> 00:53:27,207
You'll meet her tomorrow.

813
00:53:27,291 --> 00:53:29,376
- Tomorrow?
- Yes.

814
00:53:29,459 --> 00:53:31,753
Because tomorrow
is your birthday...

815
00:53:31,837 --> 00:53:34,089
and your grandma will come
and bring you a nice present.

816
00:53:34,172 --> 00:53:37,301
A new tank?

817
00:53:38,051 --> 00:53:39,553
No, a surprise.

818
00:53:39,636 --> 00:53:41,555
Give the letter to your mom.

819
00:53:43,056 --> 00:53:44,766
Bye, Joshua.

820
00:53:44,850 --> 00:53:46,643
You forgot your change,
Grandma.

821
00:53:53,442 --> 00:53:54,484
Thank you.

822
00:53:55,569 --> 00:53:57,904
- When are you coming?
- In an hour or so.

823
00:53:57,988 --> 00:54:00,782
I'm going to stop by my uncle's to see
if he'll bring some leftovers.

824
00:54:02,117 --> 00:54:05,078
- Then what did Grandma say?
- She's coming tomorrow.

825
00:54:07,664 --> 00:54:08,999
It's about time!

826
00:54:09,082 --> 00:54:11,168
J EWISH STORE

827
00:54:11,293 --> 00:54:14,004
- It's time for your bath now.
- I don't want to take one.

828
00:54:14,087 --> 00:54:17,007
- Go take a bath.
- I took one on Friday.

829
00:54:17,049 --> 00:54:18,675
He's right.

830
00:54:18,759 --> 00:54:20,719
You change your shirt.

831
00:54:20,761 --> 00:54:23,221
- I changed it on Thursday!
- Don't forget the flowers!

832
00:54:23,263 --> 00:54:25,724
They're outside.
I already picked them.

833
00:54:25,849 --> 00:54:29,811
- I'll come with you, Pop!
- You have to take a bath, stubborn!

834
00:54:29,895 --> 00:54:32,439
I don't want to take one!

835
00:54:32,564 --> 00:54:34,441
Hurry up.
I have to go pick Grandma up.

836
00:54:41,907 --> 00:54:45,285
- Where do you want the flowers?
- Set them down. I'll be right there.

837
00:54:46,578 --> 00:54:49,289
[ Hiccupping ]

838
00:54:55,629 --> 00:54:57,714
I took one on Friday!

839
00:54:58,465 --> 00:55:00,425
[ Dora ]
Joshua!

840
00:55:00,550 --> 00:55:02,427
Joshua!

841
00:55:02,886 --> 00:55:04,805
Do you know where Joshua is?

842
00:55:04,930 --> 00:55:06,974
He must be in there.

843
00:55:07,099 --> 00:55:08,976
Will you put those things
in order?

844
00:55:09,101 --> 00:55:11,270
Why don't you show me the flowers?
They look so beautiful.

845
00:55:11,395 --> 00:55:14,064
They are. I'll bring them right over.
You want to see the flowers?

846
00:55:14,147 --> 00:55:18,402
I'll make them come right over.
Come, flowers!

847
00:55:18,568 --> 00:55:20,237
Come, nightstand!

848
00:55:20,362 --> 00:55:23,323
Schopenhauer, willpower,
I want the nightstand to come here.

849
00:55:23,407 --> 00:55:25,993
Nightstand, come.

850
00:55:27,411 --> 00:55:29,871
Stop, nightstand!

851
00:55:29,955 --> 00:55:33,208
The nightstand seems
very dirty to me.

852
00:55:33,292 --> 00:55:36,587
Good morning, Princess!

853
00:55:36,670 --> 00:55:39,381
[ Hoof beats Approaching ]

854
00:55:40,966 --> 00:55:43,051
He can already read and write?

855
00:55:43,135 --> 00:55:45,762
- For over a year now.
- You did a good job.

856
00:55:45,846 --> 00:55:47,931
We're here.

857
00:55:48,015 --> 00:55:50,058
I'll help you get out.

858
00:55:50,142 --> 00:55:52,060
No, I can do it myself.

859
00:56:09,661 --> 00:56:11,872
Dora, what's wrong?

860
00:56:32,184 --> 00:56:34,102
Are we there?

861
00:56:34,186 --> 00:56:36,605
No, it's a crossing.

862
00:56:38,523 --> 00:56:42,069
[ Meowing ]
- Will you tell me
where we're going now?

863
00:56:42,152 --> 00:56:44,613
What do you mean, where?

864
00:56:44,696 --> 00:56:47,658
You asked me a thousand times.
We're going...

865
00:56:47,741 --> 00:56:50,327
to the place--
What's it called?

866
00:56:50,452 --> 00:56:52,162
We're going--

867
00:56:52,245 --> 00:56:54,498
Where are we going?

868
00:56:54,581 --> 00:56:58,502
What day is it today?
Today is your birthday!

869
00:56:58,585 --> 00:57:01,129
You've always said
you wanted to go on a trip!

870
00:57:01,213 --> 00:57:04,341
It took me months
to plan this whole thing.

871
00:57:05,592 --> 00:57:07,844
You know where we're going?

872
00:57:07,970 --> 00:57:10,681
I can't tell you.
I promised Mom I wouldn't tell.

873
00:57:10,806 --> 00:57:12,641
You know how she is.
She'll get mad.

874
00:57:12,724 --> 00:57:14,851
It makes me laugh.

875
00:57:14,935 --> 00:57:18,355
My pop planned something like this
for me when I was little too.

876
00:57:21,108 --> 00:57:23,193
It was so--
Boy, it was funny!

877
00:57:27,197 --> 00:57:30,659
I'm not going to tell you.
I want you to see for yourself.

878
00:57:30,784 --> 00:57:34,246
It's a surprise.
You know, it's really--

879
00:57:34,329 --> 00:57:35,831
It really makes me laugh.

880
00:57:35,956 --> 00:57:38,375
[ Meowing ]
- I'm tired.

881
00:57:38,458 --> 00:57:40,419
Go to sleep.

882
00:57:46,300 --> 00:57:49,261
Where are we going?
Where are they taking us?

883
00:58:06,194 --> 00:58:08,071
[ Man Shouting In German ]

884
00:58:08,989 --> 00:58:12,826
What time is it?
We're leaving right on time.

885
00:58:12,909 --> 00:58:14,661
What organization!

886
00:58:14,745 --> 00:58:17,414
- You've never taken a train, huh?
- No. Is it nice?

887
00:58:17,497 --> 00:58:18,999
It's really nice!

888
00:58:19,082 --> 00:58:22,336
It's all wooden inside. Everybody
stands up. There's not one seat.

889
00:58:22,419 --> 00:58:25,756
- There aren't any seats?
- What? Seats on a train?

890
00:58:25,839 --> 00:58:28,050
It's obvious
you've never been on one!

891
00:58:28,133 --> 00:58:31,386
No, everybody
stands real close together.

892
00:58:31,470 --> 00:58:35,682
Do you see this line?
I got the last tickets just in time!

893
00:58:35,766 --> 00:58:39,102
Hurry up, Uncle Eliseo.
I don't want them to say, "Too late.

894
00:58:39,227 --> 00:58:40,854
It's full.
Go back home."

895
00:58:40,938 --> 00:58:44,441
Wait up. We've got a reservation!
Leave some room for us!

896
00:58:44,566 --> 00:58:46,485
Look at this line!

897
00:58:48,236 --> 00:58:51,031
Here we are!
We made a reservation!

898
00:58:53,575 --> 00:58:55,786
Thank you!

899
00:58:58,372 --> 00:59:03,126
- May I help you?
- There's been a mistake.

900
00:59:03,251 --> 00:59:05,754
What mistake?

901
00:59:05,879 --> 00:59:08,632
My husband and son
are on that train.

902
00:59:09,758 --> 00:59:11,635
What's your husband's name?

903
00:59:11,718 --> 00:59:13,929
Guido Orefice.

904
00:59:20,018 --> 00:59:21,812
Joshua Orefice...

905
00:59:21,895 --> 00:59:25,941
and Eliseo Orefice
are on that train too.

906
00:59:26,024 --> 00:59:27,943
There's no mistake.

907
00:59:29,778 --> 00:59:31,780
I want to get
on that train too.

908
00:59:33,740 --> 00:59:37,494
- We're all ready.
- Send them off then.

909
00:59:37,577 --> 00:59:38,954
Go, leave!

910
00:59:41,206 --> 00:59:44,501
[ Whistle Blowing ]
- Go back home, ma'am.

911
00:59:44,584 --> 00:59:46,169
I want to get on that train.

912
00:59:46,295 --> 00:59:48,171
[ Train Whistle Blowing ]

913
00:59:55,095 --> 00:59:57,848
Let me get on that train!

914
01:00:03,020 --> 01:00:06,106
[ Speaking German ]
[ Whistle Blows ]

915
01:00:08,400 --> 01:00:11,194
[ Brakes Hissing ]

916
01:00:28,712 --> 01:00:29,713
Mom's here!

917
01:00:31,757 --> 01:00:36,386
- Dora.
- They stopped the train
to let Mom get on.

918
01:00:37,471 --> 01:00:39,514
[ German ]

919
01:00:52,444 --> 01:00:56,365
[ Shouting In German ]
[ Whistle Blowing ]

920
01:01:00,285 --> 01:01:03,205
[ Train Whistle Blowing ]

921
01:01:17,719 --> 01:01:20,639
[ Door Unlocking ]

922
01:01:27,104 --> 01:01:30,023
[ Engine Chugging ]

923
01:01:58,176 --> 01:02:01,096
[ Brakes Screeching ]

924
01:02:06,643 --> 01:02:09,438
[ Woman Shouting In German ]
[ Man Shouting In German ]

925
01:02:39,718 --> 01:02:41,261
Uncle Eliseo.

926
01:02:55,651 --> 01:02:57,611
Dora!

927
01:03:00,447 --> 01:03:02,783
Dora!

928
01:03:04,826 --> 01:03:07,329
[ Shouting In German ]

929
01:03:21,468 --> 01:03:24,846
Are you happy? Did you see this place?
Are you tired?

930
01:03:24,972 --> 01:03:28,350
- I didn't like the train.
- Me either.

931
01:03:28,475 --> 01:03:30,644
We'll take the bus back.

932
01:03:30,769 --> 01:03:35,023
We're taking the bus back!
The one with the seats in it!

933
01:03:35,148 --> 01:03:37,985
- I told them.
- It's better.

934
01:03:39,152 --> 01:03:42,322
You see?
It's all organized!

935
01:03:42,447 --> 01:03:46,868
Did you see that line?
People are lined up to get inside!

936
01:03:46,994 --> 01:03:50,497
- Everybody wants to get in!
- What game is this?

937
01:03:50,622 --> 01:03:52,332
That's it!

938
01:03:52,457 --> 01:03:54,960
It's that game where--

939
01:03:55,002 --> 01:03:57,379
It's the game--

940
01:03:57,504 --> 01:03:59,381
We're all players.

941
01:04:00,841 --> 01:04:03,468
It's all organized.
The game is...

942
01:04:03,510 --> 01:04:06,680
the men are over here,
the women are over there.

943
01:04:06,805 --> 01:04:09,975
Then there's the soldiers.
They give us our schedule.

944
01:04:10,017 --> 01:04:12,519
It's hard, you know.
It's not easy.

945
01:04:12,644 --> 01:04:16,356
If somebody makes a mistake,
they get sent right home.

946
01:04:16,481 --> 01:04:18,483
That means you have to be
very careful.

947
01:04:18,525 --> 01:04:22,029
But if you win,
you get first prize!

948
01:04:22,154 --> 01:04:24,406
What's the prize?

949
01:04:24,531 --> 01:04:26,491
First prize!

950
01:04:27,993 --> 01:04:31,038
- It's a tank.
- I already have one.

951
01:04:31,163 --> 01:04:34,833
This one's a real tank!
Brand new!

952
01:04:34,916 --> 01:04:37,085
Real?

953
01:04:37,210 --> 01:04:39,921
Yes!
I didn't want to tell you.

954
01:04:41,840 --> 01:04:44,760
[ German ]

955
01:04:47,429 --> 01:04:49,389
Where's Uncle Eliseo going?

956
01:04:49,514 --> 01:04:52,059
He's on another team.
It's all organized.

957
01:04:52,184 --> 01:04:54,269
Bye, Uncle!

958
01:04:57,064 --> 01:04:59,566
A real tank.

959
01:05:13,413 --> 01:05:15,248
What did I tell you?

960
01:05:16,208 --> 01:05:17,793
Fabulous!

961
01:05:17,918 --> 01:05:19,920
What a place!

962
01:05:20,045 --> 01:05:24,216
Hurry up or they'll steal our places.
We've got a reservation. Two singles!

963
01:05:25,258 --> 01:05:27,594
Coming through!

964
01:05:27,719 --> 01:05:30,055
There's our place!

965
01:05:35,227 --> 01:05:37,271
This is our bed.
We'll sleep real close.

966
01:05:39,398 --> 01:05:42,985
It's ugly here. It smells.
I want to be with Mommy.

967
01:05:43,110 --> 01:05:45,112
We will be!

968
01:05:45,237 --> 01:05:47,948
- I'm hungry!
- We'll eat!

969
01:05:48,073 --> 01:05:51,326
Plus they're really mean here!
They yell!

970
01:05:51,451 --> 01:05:55,455
They yell because everybody wants
first prize. They have to be tough.

971
01:05:55,580 --> 01:06:00,460
- Can I see Mommy?
- When the game's over.

972
01:06:00,502 --> 01:06:01,837
When's it over?

973
01:06:03,922 --> 01:06:06,300
You have to get
a thousand points.

974
01:06:07,759 --> 01:06:10,345
Whoever gets a thousand points
wins a tank.

975
01:06:10,470 --> 01:06:13,307
I don't believe you.
Are we getting a snack?

976
01:06:13,348 --> 01:06:15,851
A snack?

977
01:06:15,976 --> 01:06:18,812
Just ask.
We're all friends here.

978
01:06:18,854 --> 01:06:21,690
- Look who's here. What's his name?
- Bartolomeo.

979
01:06:21,815 --> 01:06:23,942
Let me ask you something.

980
01:06:24,026 --> 01:06:27,195
Did the guy who hands out
the bread and jam already come by?

981
01:06:28,614 --> 01:06:32,159
Darn it all!
We missed him by a second!

982
01:06:32,284 --> 01:06:35,787
He'll come back again though,
won't he?

983
01:06:35,829 --> 01:06:38,540
He's coming back.

984
01:06:41,001 --> 01:06:43,629
[ German ]

985
01:06:44,838 --> 01:06:47,841
- What did he say?
- He asked if anyone speaks German.

986
01:06:47,966 --> 01:06:50,135
He's going to explain
the camp's rules.

987
01:06:53,555 --> 01:06:55,807
- Do you speak German?
- No.

988
01:07:02,648 --> 01:07:04,691
[ German ]

989
01:07:05,317 --> 01:07:08,695
The game starts now. Whoever's here
is here, whoever's not is not.

990
01:07:08,820 --> 01:07:10,989
[ German Continues ]

991
01:07:12,324 --> 01:07:16,036
The first one to get a thousand points
wins. The prize is a tank!

992
01:07:17,162 --> 01:07:18,205
Lucky him!

993
01:07:26,880 --> 01:07:30,884
Every day we'll announce who's in
the lead from that loudspeaker.

994
01:07:31,009 --> 01:07:33,887
The one with the least points
has to wear a sign saying "jackass"...

995
01:07:33,929 --> 01:07:35,263
right here on his back.

996
01:07:35,389 --> 01:07:39,851
[ German Continues ]

997
01:07:42,354 --> 01:07:45,232
We play the part
of the real mean guys who yell.

998
01:07:45,274 --> 01:07:46,733
Whoever's scared loses points.

999
01:08:02,082 --> 01:08:05,585
You'll lose your points
for three things.

1000
01:08:05,711 --> 01:08:08,714
One, if you cry.

1001
01:08:08,755 --> 01:08:11,717
Two, if you want
to see your mommy.

1002
01:08:11,758 --> 01:08:15,220
Three, if you're hungry
and you want a snack.

1003
01:08:15,304 --> 01:08:16,888
Forget about it!

1004
01:08:25,564 --> 01:08:28,108
It's easy to lose points
for being hungry.

1005
01:08:28,233 --> 01:08:30,402
Just yesterday
I lost 40 points...

1006
01:08:30,485 --> 01:08:33,280
because I absolutely had
to have a jam sandwich.

1007
01:08:34,740 --> 01:08:38,285
Apricot jam!
He wanted strawberry.

1008
01:08:45,917 --> 01:08:48,629
Don't ask for any lollipops.
You won't get any.

1009
01:08:48,754 --> 01:08:50,339
We eat them all!

1010
01:08:52,466 --> 01:08:53,967
I ate 20 of them yesterday!

1011
01:08:55,093 --> 01:08:58,764
What a stomachache.
But they sure were good.

1012
01:08:59,848 --> 01:09:00,932
You bet.

1013
01:09:09,650 --> 01:09:12,486
Sorry if I'm going so fast,
but I'm playing hide-and-seek.

1014
01:09:12,527 --> 01:09:14,488
I have to go now
or they'll find me.

1015
01:09:14,529 --> 01:09:17,115
[ Indistinct Chattering ]
[ Door Shuts ]

1016
01:09:24,498 --> 01:09:28,502
Don't ask me anything.
Ask Bartolomeo. He knows everything.

1017
01:09:28,627 --> 01:09:31,004
Don't forget to tell me
what he said too.

1018
01:09:31,046 --> 01:09:33,006
A thousand points?

1019
01:09:33,131 --> 01:09:35,467
I told you we're going
to have fun!

1020
01:09:35,634 --> 01:09:37,844
These guys are crazy!

1021
01:09:37,970 --> 01:09:41,848
This has to weigh a hundred kilos!
It's got to be 3,000 degrees in here!

1022
01:09:41,974 --> 01:09:44,476
Vittorino, I can't cope anymore!

1023
01:09:44,518 --> 01:09:47,396
- After only the first one?
- Why, are there more to move?

1024
01:09:47,521 --> 01:09:49,815
We're here until tonight!

1025
01:09:49,856 --> 01:09:53,235
Bartolomeo, what happened?
Where are they taking you?

1026
01:09:53,360 --> 01:09:56,029
To the hospital.
I hurt my arm.

1027
01:09:57,531 --> 01:09:59,658
We're going to die here!

1028
01:10:00,826 --> 01:10:03,829
I can't take it anymore!
I'm putting this down.

1029
01:10:03,870 --> 01:10:06,373
I'll tell them I can't do it.
What can they do to me?

1030
01:10:06,498 --> 01:10:09,042
They'll kill you!

1031
01:10:11,503 --> 01:10:13,547
- Where does this thing go?
- Down there.

1032
01:10:13,672 --> 01:10:16,341
Good Lord!
I'll never make it!

1033
01:10:24,558 --> 01:10:26,852
It's got to be
1 0,000 degrees in here!

1034
01:10:47,080 --> 01:10:50,042
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

1035
01:10:57,215 --> 01:10:58,550
Pop!

1036
01:11:14,066 --> 01:11:17,069
Look here! See?
It's nice, huh?

1037
01:11:19,529 --> 01:11:21,698
We're signed up.

1038
01:11:21,740 --> 01:11:25,077
When I got there to sign up...

1039
01:11:25,202 --> 01:11:27,955
the referee was there
and he said...

1040
01:11:28,080 --> 01:11:30,791
" No, you and your son
aren't on the list.

1041
01:11:30,916 --> 01:11:33,251
You didn't pay your dues."

1042
01:11:33,377 --> 01:11:35,379
I almost fell over.

1043
01:11:35,462 --> 01:11:38,632
He said, "You can go home."
I said, " No, you go home!

1044
01:11:38,757 --> 01:11:41,468
Joshua and I signed up.

1045
01:11:41,593 --> 01:11:46,556
Give me my number!"
In fact, they gave me one. Look.

1046
01:11:46,598 --> 01:11:50,310
I had them put it here, too,
just in case.

1047
01:11:50,435 --> 01:11:52,479
See what a nice place...

1048
01:11:53,605 --> 01:11:55,649
your pop takes you to?

1049
01:11:57,776 --> 01:12:00,570
Did you play with
the other kids?

1050
01:12:00,612 --> 01:12:03,282
Yes, but they don't
know the rules.

1051
01:12:04,157 --> 01:12:07,077
They said it isn't true that
first prize is a tank.

1052
01:12:07,119 --> 01:12:09,329
They don't know anything
about the points.

1053
01:12:09,454 --> 01:12:12,958
Did you fall for that?
They're as sly as foxes.

1054
01:12:13,083 --> 01:12:15,085
They want to beat you!
Are you joking?

1055
01:12:15,168 --> 01:12:18,797
There's no tank?
Don't you believe them!

1056
01:12:18,922 --> 01:12:21,800
How many points
did we get today?

1057
01:12:21,925 --> 01:12:23,802
Fifty.

1058
01:12:23,844 --> 01:12:26,805
Forty-eight. They took two points
away from me because...

1059
01:12:26,847 --> 01:12:29,099
I tripped while I was...

1060
01:12:29,141 --> 01:12:31,435
playing hopscotch.

1061
01:12:32,602 --> 01:12:34,271
We...

1062
01:12:34,354 --> 01:12:38,150
Laughed like crazy today!
I died laughing!

1063
01:12:38,275 --> 01:12:40,152
Boy, did I have fun!

1064
01:12:40,277 --> 01:12:42,654
I can't wait to start
all over again tomorrow!

1065
01:12:42,779 --> 01:12:46,491
Hopscotch, tug-of-war
and ring-around-the-rosy.

1066
01:12:46,617 --> 01:12:48,869
Every game.
I don't even remember all of them.

1067
01:12:48,994 --> 01:12:52,664
"You guys are obsessed! Stop!
I'm tired!" I said.

1068
01:12:52,789 --> 01:12:54,666
Listen.

1069
01:12:54,791 --> 01:12:58,337
- Did you eat something?
- Yes, but I didn't ask for a snack.

1070
01:12:58,462 --> 01:13:02,466
Good boy!
That means you got 1 2 points too!

1071
01:13:02,549 --> 01:13:04,885
Forty-eight for me, 1 2 for you.

1072
01:13:05,010 --> 01:13:06,303
Sixty points.

1073
01:13:06,345 --> 01:13:09,556
This is what you get
when you get up to 60.

1074
01:13:09,681 --> 01:13:13,018
A plain piece of bread,
no jam.

1075
01:13:13,143 --> 01:13:15,228
Here, eat this.

1076
01:13:15,354 --> 01:13:17,731
Grazie.

1077
01:13:17,856 --> 01:13:21,485
- Is 60 points a lot?
- Are you kidding?

1078
01:13:21,526 --> 01:13:23,070
It sure is!

1079
01:13:26,865 --> 01:13:29,368
Look who's here!
Bartolomeo!

1080
01:13:29,493 --> 01:13:30,535
How'd it go?

1081
01:13:31,870 --> 01:13:34,873
Any worse than this--
I got 20 of them.

1082
01:13:38,669 --> 01:13:41,338
We got more than him.

1083
01:13:41,380 --> 01:13:43,757
Don't tell him that.
We're in the lead!

1084
01:13:53,558 --> 01:13:56,186
I already told you:
no children or old ladies!

1085
01:13:56,228 --> 01:13:59,231
Back inside!
You don't work!

1086
01:13:59,356 --> 01:14:01,900
The rest, downstairs!

1087
01:14:02,025 --> 01:14:04,945
Let's go, girls, quickly.
Come on. This way!

1088
01:14:06,280 --> 01:14:09,032
That one's new.
She learned right away.

1089
01:14:09,116 --> 01:14:12,619
The lady at the door,
she seemed nice when she first came.

1090
01:14:12,744 --> 01:14:14,579
She's the worst of all!

1091
01:14:14,621 --> 01:14:17,416
At least she didn't send
the old ladies and children to work.

1092
01:14:17,541 --> 01:14:21,086
They don't send old people and kids
to work because they kill them!

1093
01:14:21,211 --> 01:14:23,922
One of these days
they'll call them to take a shower.

1094
01:14:24,047 --> 01:14:25,882
"Children, shower time!"

1095
01:14:25,924 --> 01:14:29,469
The truth is, they make them
shower there in the gas chamber.

1096
01:14:36,893 --> 01:14:38,562
Downstairs!

1097
01:14:42,399 --> 01:14:45,235
How can I do this?

1098
01:14:45,277 --> 01:14:46,903
Vittorino!

1099
01:14:48,322 --> 01:14:50,782
Where'd they find
all these anvils?

1100
01:14:50,907 --> 01:14:52,784
Pop!

1101
01:14:54,453 --> 01:14:56,955
Why are you here?
You're not supposed to be here!

1102
01:14:57,080 --> 01:14:58,790
Go away!

1103
01:14:58,915 --> 01:15:01,293
Why aren't you with
the other kids?

1104
01:15:01,335 --> 01:15:03,128
They said...

1105
01:15:03,253 --> 01:15:06,340
all us kids have to take
a shower today, and I don't want to.

1106
01:15:07,966 --> 01:15:09,968
- Go take a shower!
- No!

1107
01:15:11,011 --> 01:15:13,013
I'm not going to.

1108
01:15:13,138 --> 01:15:14,640
Go take a shower!

1109
01:15:15,766 --> 01:15:17,309
What are you doing here?

1110
01:15:19,603 --> 01:15:24,316
We're making... a tank.

1111
01:15:24,441 --> 01:15:27,653
We're building the tank.
We're still working on the tracks.

1112
01:15:27,778 --> 01:15:29,655
We're running slow.

1113
01:15:31,323 --> 01:15:34,368
You can't stay here.
Go take your shower!

1114
01:15:34,493 --> 01:15:37,496
I don't want to!

1115
01:15:37,621 --> 01:15:41,333
You stubborn thing! I'll tell Mom!
Ten points off for you!

1116
01:15:41,458 --> 01:15:44,670
Hide behind there.
We'll go back together when I'm done.

1117
01:15:44,795 --> 01:15:46,672
Don't let anyone see you!

1118
01:15:46,797 --> 01:15:48,674
This sure is fun.

1119
01:15:51,468 --> 01:15:54,346
[ Shouting In German ]

1120
01:15:54,471 --> 01:15:57,349
[ Child Crying ]

1121
01:16:02,813 --> 01:16:04,231
Everything!

1122
01:16:04,356 --> 01:16:06,900
Take everything off!.
Hang it up there!

1123
01:16:07,025 --> 01:16:10,195
You'll get it back
after the shower.

1124
01:16:10,320 --> 01:16:11,571
Forward!

1125
01:16:13,532 --> 01:16:16,034
Remember your number
to get your clothes back!

1126
01:16:19,579 --> 01:16:22,749
Women and children
will shower together.

1127
01:16:22,874 --> 01:16:24,876
Are you hurt?

1128
01:16:35,762 --> 01:16:37,723
Thanks, Bartolomeo.

1129
01:16:37,848 --> 01:16:40,726
From now on, you have to
hide here the whole day.

1130
01:16:40,851 --> 01:16:43,395
If they see us now it's over.
We're disqualified.

1131
01:16:43,520 --> 01:16:45,272
What do I have to do?

1132
01:16:45,397 --> 01:16:47,733
You have to stay.
Vittorino, help me out.

1133
01:16:47,858 --> 01:16:49,860
You have to hide here all day.

1134
01:16:49,943 --> 01:16:54,364
Don't let anyone see you,
especially those mean guys who yell.

1135
01:16:54,406 --> 01:16:55,741
Remember.

1136
01:16:55,866 --> 01:16:57,743
Stay hidden!

1137
01:16:57,784 --> 01:17:00,454
This is the hardest part.

1138
01:17:00,579 --> 01:17:05,125
If we get this right, the tank is ours.
It's worth 1 20 points a day.

1139
01:17:05,250 --> 01:17:08,086
I'll take you with me.
I'll hide you. You're gone.

1140
01:17:08,211 --> 01:17:11,089
Who's ever seen you before?
Who are you? Where is he?

1141
01:17:11,214 --> 01:17:12,591
Got it?

1142
01:17:12,633 --> 01:17:14,092
Joshua?

1143
01:17:17,804 --> 01:17:19,056
Gotya!

1144
01:17:20,891 --> 01:17:22,267
Good boy!

1145
01:17:48,627 --> 01:17:51,588
[ Meowing ]

1146
01:17:54,007 --> 01:17:57,177
[ Man On P.A. Speaking In German ]

1147
01:18:05,102 --> 01:18:08,021
[ Hiccupping ]

1148
01:18:39,219 --> 01:18:41,805
Anybody here?
Am I disturbing?

1149
01:18:44,558 --> 01:18:48,520
[ Hiccupping ]
-Joshua!

1150
01:18:49,980 --> 01:18:52,065
Come here!

1151
01:18:52,190 --> 01:18:54,151
Quick as lightning!

1152
01:19:00,157 --> 01:19:01,867
Good morning, Princess!

1153
01:19:01,992 --> 01:19:06,038
Last night,
I dreamt about you all night!

1154
01:19:06,163 --> 01:19:10,542
We were going to the movies.
You were wearing that pink suit...

1155
01:19:10,584 --> 01:19:12,252
that I really like.

1156
01:19:12,377 --> 01:19:14,713
You're all I think about,
Princess.

1157
01:19:14,838 --> 01:19:17,424
I always think about you.
And now--

1158
01:19:17,549 --> 01:19:19,051
Mommy!

1159
01:19:19,176 --> 01:19:23,180
Pop wheelsmein the wheelbarrow,
but he doesn't know how to drive!

1160
01:19:23,263 --> 01:19:24,723
We laugh like crazy!

1161
01:19:24,848 --> 01:19:28,685
We're in the lead!
How many points do we have today?

1162
01:19:28,727 --> 01:19:32,064
Run! The mean guys
who yell are behind us!

1163
01:19:32,105 --> 01:19:34,608
- Where?
- Over here! Come on!

1164
01:19:38,111 --> 01:19:40,572
[Guido's Voice Fading]

1165
01:19:48,288 --> 01:19:51,875
[ Rain Falling ]
- Are they dry?

1166
01:19:51,959 --> 01:19:53,543
They're dry.

1167
01:19:53,669 --> 01:19:55,379
Catch.

1168
01:19:55,504 --> 01:19:58,340
- Get dressed.
[ Thunderclap ]

1169
01:20:11,311 --> 01:20:14,898
What happened to Vittorino,
Alfonso and the others?

1170
01:20:14,982 --> 01:20:17,317
They didn't make it.

1171
01:20:19,403 --> 01:20:21,780
[ German ]

1172
01:20:36,211 --> 01:20:39,339
[ Thunderclap ]

1173
01:21:03,155 --> 01:21:05,741
[ Muttering ]

1174
01:21:09,620 --> 01:21:13,206
- "If you say my name,
I'm not there anymore."
[ Woman Yells ]

1175
01:21:13,290 --> 01:21:14,625
Silence.

1176
01:21:20,297 --> 01:21:22,716
The Grand Hotel.

1177
01:21:27,304 --> 01:21:29,222
Guido.

1178
01:21:33,018 --> 01:21:34,978
[ Sighs ]

1179
01:21:37,356 --> 01:21:39,900
[ Shouts ]

1180
01:21:42,361 --> 01:21:44,321
[ German ]

1181
01:21:46,698 --> 01:21:50,494
Guido. Thank goodness. I was
getting scared. What happened to you?

1182
01:21:50,619 --> 01:21:52,829
They're half crazy!

1183
01:21:55,290 --> 01:21:57,501
The man who does the checkups,
the captain--

1184
01:21:57,626 --> 01:22:00,420
He's a friend of mine.
I met him when I was a waiter.

1185
01:22:00,504 --> 01:22:04,675
He said they're having a dinner
with all the officials and their wives.

1186
01:22:04,800 --> 01:22:08,220
He asked me if I wanted to
wait tables at the dinner.

1187
01:22:08,303 --> 01:22:12,224
Maybe he wants to help me.
He might get us out of here.

1188
01:22:13,558 --> 01:22:15,477
Joshua?

1189
01:22:18,605 --> 01:22:20,774
Have you seen Joshua?

1190
01:22:20,857 --> 01:22:24,820
- What do you mean, no? Joshua?
[ Hiccupping ]

1191
01:22:24,945 --> 01:22:26,822
Joshua!

1192
01:22:30,117 --> 01:22:32,202
What are you doing?
Come here!

1193
01:22:32,285 --> 01:22:36,540
- No.
- I told you to come.

1194
01:22:36,623 --> 01:22:38,208
No? Come on out!

1195
01:22:39,293 --> 01:22:41,753
Come out! Look here.
You're all dirty.

1196
01:22:42,838 --> 01:22:44,172
Where have you been?

1197
01:22:45,424 --> 01:22:47,926
I had to finish playing rummy.

1198
01:22:48,885 --> 01:22:52,055
They make buttons and soap
out of us.

1199
01:22:54,308 --> 01:22:57,936
- What are you saying?
- They burn us all in the oven.

1200
01:22:58,937 --> 01:23:01,315
Who told you that?

1201
01:23:01,398 --> 01:23:06,236
A man was crying. He said they make
buttons and soap out of us.

1202
01:23:06,320 --> 01:23:08,238
[ Chuckling ]

1203
01:23:08,864 --> 01:23:11,033
You fell for that?

1204
01:23:11,116 --> 01:23:13,327
Again?

1205
01:23:13,410 --> 01:23:16,747
I thought you were a sharp boy--
cunning, intelligent.

1206
01:23:16,872 --> 01:23:20,792
Buttons and soap out of people?
That'll be the day!

1207
01:23:20,876 --> 01:23:23,378
You believed that?

1208
01:23:24,212 --> 01:23:28,300
Just imagine. Tomorrow morning,
I wash my hands with Bartolomeo...

1209
01:23:28,383 --> 01:23:30,052
a good scrub.

1210
01:23:30,135 --> 01:23:32,929
Then I'll button up
with Francesco.

1211
01:23:33,013 --> 01:23:34,264
Darn it all!

1212
01:23:34,348 --> 01:23:36,933
Look! I just lost Giorgio!

1213
01:23:37,017 --> 01:23:39,311
Does this look like a person?

1214
01:23:39,394 --> 01:23:42,439
Come on! They were teasing you!
And you fell for it!

1215
01:23:42,522 --> 01:23:44,775
What else did they tell you?

1216
01:23:44,900 --> 01:23:46,777
That we get cooked in the oven.

1217
01:23:49,154 --> 01:23:52,783
[ Laughing ]
- They burn us up in the oven.

1218
01:23:56,453 --> 01:23:59,581
You fell for that too!
You just eat everything up!

1219
01:23:59,665 --> 01:24:01,959
I've heard of a wood oven...

1220
01:24:02,042 --> 01:24:04,086
but I've never seen
a man oven before.

1221
01:24:05,003 --> 01:24:08,799
"I'm made of wood!"
"Take this lawyer!"

1222
01:24:08,924 --> 01:24:11,385
"This lawyer doesn't burn.
He's not dry enough.

1223
01:24:11,468 --> 01:24:13,136
Look at that smoke!"

1224
01:24:14,680 --> 01:24:17,474
Buttons, soap,
we get burned in the oven.

1225
01:24:17,557 --> 01:24:19,643
Let's be serious now.

1226
01:24:19,726 --> 01:24:22,521
I have a bag race
with the bad guys tomorrow.

1227
01:24:22,604 --> 01:24:26,149
That's enough.
I want to go home.

1228
01:24:27,985 --> 01:24:30,654
- Now?
- Right now.

1229
01:24:30,737 --> 01:24:33,991
It's raining now. You'll come down
with a terrible fever!

1230
01:24:34,074 --> 01:24:35,951
I don't care.
Let's go.

1231
01:24:37,244 --> 01:24:39,788
All right.
If you want to go--

1232
01:24:41,039 --> 01:24:42,958
I'll get our stuff
and we'll leave.

1233
01:24:44,209 --> 01:24:46,503
- We can leave?
- Naturally.

1234
01:24:46,586 --> 01:24:49,089
What do you think they do,
force people to stay here?

1235
01:24:49,172 --> 01:24:51,216
That'll be the day.

1236
01:24:51,300 --> 01:24:54,344
Wouldn't that be great?
Let's go. We'll pack our bags...

1237
01:24:54,428 --> 01:24:57,097
and get out of here.

1238
01:24:57,180 --> 01:25:00,976
What a shame. We were in the lead.
We're quitting. Off the list we go.

1239
01:25:01,059 --> 01:25:04,104
Some other kid
will win the real tank.

1240
01:25:04,187 --> 01:25:07,190
There aren't any other kids.
I'm the only one left.

1241
01:25:07,274 --> 01:25:10,527
There aren't any more kids?
It's chock-full of them here!

1242
01:25:10,610 --> 01:25:12,154
Where are they then?

1243
01:25:12,237 --> 01:25:15,032
They're all hiding.
Nobody's supposed to see them.

1244
01:25:15,115 --> 01:25:19,119
- This is a serious game!
- I just don't get it.

1245
01:25:19,202 --> 01:25:21,204
How many points do we have?

1246
01:25:21,288 --> 01:25:23,415
Almost 687.

1247
01:25:23,498 --> 01:25:25,500
I told you a thousand times.

1248
01:25:26,293 --> 01:25:27,753
Let's go, though.

1249
01:25:27,836 --> 01:25:30,839
- We're winning, but if you want--
- We're winning?

1250
01:25:30,922 --> 01:25:35,385
We're first, I told you.
But we'll quit if you want.

1251
01:25:36,219 --> 01:25:39,222
I saw the chart yesterday.
We'll go anyway, though.

1252
01:25:39,306 --> 01:25:41,224
Bye, Bartolomeo.
Joshua and I are leaving.

1253
01:25:41,308 --> 01:25:43,143
We're fed up here.

1254
01:25:44,811 --> 01:25:47,397
The tank is done.
It's ready.

1255
01:25:47,481 --> 01:25:50,400
Clean the spark plugs off
before you start it.

1256
01:25:50,484 --> 01:25:53,195
Open the throttle...

1257
01:25:53,278 --> 01:25:56,406
otherwise the cannon will
get stuck with the tracks.

1258
01:25:56,490 --> 01:26:00,702
And the gun. Did you see
how nice it is? It came out beautiful!

1259
01:26:00,786 --> 01:26:04,581
Lift the emergency brake off
before you move! We're going.

1260
01:26:04,665 --> 01:26:06,750
Joshua wants to quit.

1261
01:26:06,833 --> 01:26:10,337
We could have gone back with a tank
soon, but we'll take the bus today.

1262
01:26:10,420 --> 01:26:12,756
Joshua and I are leaving.
So long, everybody!

1263
01:26:12,839 --> 01:26:14,758
We're tired of this place.

1264
01:26:14,841 --> 01:26:17,594
Let's go or we'll miss the bus.

1265
01:26:23,433 --> 01:26:24,893
Let's go, Joshua.

1266
01:26:28,313 --> 01:26:32,109
It's raining. I'll come down
with a terrible fever!

1267
01:26:38,532 --> 01:26:43,912
[ Man On P.A. Speaking German ]

1268
01:26:57,217 --> 01:27:00,137
[ Man On P.A. Continues ]
[ Boy Speaking German ]

1269
01:27:01,179 --> 01:27:03,849
[ Counting In German ]

1270
01:27:06,643 --> 01:27:10,605
[ Boy Continues ]
[ Crowd Cheering On P.A. ]

1271
01:27:16,486 --> 01:27:18,947
[ Footsteps Marching ]

1272
01:27:21,033 --> 01:27:23,994
[ Shouting In German ]

1273
01:27:40,344 --> 01:27:42,304
Joshua?

1274
01:27:42,471 --> 01:27:44,765
It's me, Pop!

1275
01:27:44,848 --> 01:27:48,018
I have to tell you
something important! Come here!

1276
01:27:48,101 --> 01:27:50,812
That little rascal's been
running away all morning.

1277
01:27:50,896 --> 01:27:53,607
- Is there really a kid?
- There must be two thousand!

1278
01:27:53,690 --> 01:27:55,817
They're like mice.
They hide all over the place!

1279
01:27:55,901 --> 01:27:58,695
Those creeps want our tank!
Stop!

1280
01:27:58,779 --> 01:28:00,197
Wait.

1281
01:28:02,032 --> 01:28:03,992
I might have spotted him.

1282
01:28:04,076 --> 01:28:06,536
I think he's nearby.

1283
01:28:06,620 --> 01:28:10,666
Look. Go see if he's hiding in there.
I'll wait here.

1284
01:28:10,749 --> 01:28:12,793
I'll keep a watch out.

1285
01:28:14,586 --> 01:28:18,256
[ German ]

1286
01:28:19,299 --> 01:28:20,968
He's there, Pop!

1287
01:28:21,051 --> 01:28:23,178
- What'd he look like? Blond?
- Yes.

1288
01:28:23,261 --> 01:28:25,931
That's him then.
His name is... Schwanz.

1289
01:28:26,014 --> 01:28:28,225
He's been in there
for three weeks.

1290
01:28:28,308 --> 01:28:30,852
He was the runner-up.
We beat him, though!

1291
01:28:30,978 --> 01:28:33,855
Sooner or later,
I'll find the others too.

1292
01:28:33,939 --> 01:28:36,525
- How many are there?
- It's swarming, I told you.

1293
01:28:36,650 --> 01:28:38,360
They're all hidden.

1294
01:28:38,485 --> 01:28:40,445
[ Shouting In German ]

1295
01:28:47,786 --> 01:28:50,747
- Look, Pop!
- There's a hideout!

1296
01:28:52,749 --> 01:28:54,710
Gotya, got ya, got ya!
You're out! Let's go.

1297
01:28:57,295 --> 01:28:59,339
Come here! Come here!

1298
01:29:02,134 --> 01:29:05,512
- Holy smokes! She saw us!
- Are we out?

1299
01:29:05,595 --> 01:29:08,056
She's coming over for you.

1300
01:29:08,140 --> 01:29:10,058
Now it's time for
the "be quiet" game.

1301
01:29:10,142 --> 01:29:13,061
You're never to speak.

1302
01:29:13,145 --> 01:29:14,896
Swear it!

1303
01:29:15,981 --> 01:29:18,066
- Swear it!
- I swear.

1304
01:29:21,111 --> 01:29:23,572
They all talk strange.
You can't understand a word.

1305
01:29:23,655 --> 01:29:26,241
If we get through this,
the first prize is ours.

1306
01:29:26,325 --> 01:29:29,369
They're rounding up everyone in
first place. It's the silence game.

1307
01:29:29,453 --> 01:29:30,746
Not a word, got it?

1308
01:29:38,670 --> 01:29:40,589
Why are you here
with the children?

1309
01:29:40,672 --> 01:29:42,591
Quiet!
You're never to speak.

1310
01:29:44,009 --> 01:29:45,302
I swear.

1311
01:30:01,526 --> 01:30:04,488
[ Children Shouting ]

1312
01:30:10,410 --> 01:30:12,788
[ Man Shouting In German ]

1313
01:30:41,400 --> 01:30:44,361
I have to talk to you.
Very important.

1314
01:30:44,444 --> 01:30:47,489
- Where? When?
- I'll signal you. Later.

1315
01:31:00,669 --> 01:31:02,004
Thank you.

1316
01:31:07,759 --> 01:31:09,720
[ German ]

1317
01:31:33,410 --> 01:31:37,956
[ Guido Speaking Italian ]
[ Children ] "Grazie. "

1318
01:31:38,040 --> 01:31:42,711
- "Grazie. Grazie. "
[Together] "Grazie. Grazie. "

1319
01:31:46,048 --> 01:31:47,966
[ Shouts ]

1320
01:31:48,425 --> 01:31:50,886
I told you not to talk
to the children.

1321
01:31:51,511 --> 01:31:56,224
[ German ]

1322
01:32:00,270 --> 01:32:03,190
[ Classical ]

1323
01:32:07,027 --> 01:32:09,237
[ Woman Speaking German ]

1324
01:32:18,789 --> 01:32:21,541
Doctor, my wife is here too.

1325
01:32:25,921 --> 01:32:28,840
[ Man Speaking German ]

1326
01:32:44,106 --> 01:32:45,607
Slowly.

1327
01:32:45,691 --> 01:32:48,276
Eat slowly.
It's bad for you.

1328
01:32:48,360 --> 01:32:52,447
We're in the lead.
We just might leave early.

1329
01:32:52,531 --> 01:32:54,783
The game finishes early.

1330
01:32:54,866 --> 01:32:57,869
Don't make a mistake
now that we're in the lead.

1331
01:32:57,953 --> 01:32:59,371
Slowly.

1332
01:33:21,601 --> 01:33:23,520
So.
Pay attention.

1333
01:33:29,234 --> 01:33:33,196
" Fat, fat, ugly, ugly,
all yellow in reality.

1334
01:33:34,906 --> 01:33:36,992
If you ask me what I am...

1335
01:33:37,075 --> 01:33:39,828
I answer, 'Cheep, cheep, cheep.'

1336
01:33:45,542 --> 01:33:49,087
Walking along I go,
'Poopoo'.

1337
01:33:49,171 --> 01:33:51,673
Who am l?
Tell me true."

1338
01:33:56,178 --> 01:33:58,013
A duckling, right?

1339
01:34:01,099 --> 01:34:03,018
Is it a duckling?

1340
01:34:04,603 --> 01:34:07,189
It's not!

1341
01:34:08,190 --> 01:34:11,526
A veterinarian friend of mine
sent it to me from Vienna.

1342
01:34:11,610 --> 01:34:14,112
I can't send him mine...

1343
01:34:14,196 --> 01:34:16,698
until I solve this one.

1344
01:34:17,783 --> 01:34:19,868
I thought...

1345
01:34:19,951 --> 01:34:22,204
duck-billed platypus...

1346
01:34:22,287 --> 01:34:24,331
but it doesn't go,
"Cheep, cheep, cheep."

1347
01:34:24,414 --> 01:34:26,750
A duck-billed platypus goes--

1348
01:34:26,833 --> 01:34:28,752
[ Blowing ]

1349
01:34:32,464 --> 01:34:36,218
I translated it into Italian
for you last night.

1350
01:34:38,178 --> 01:34:40,097
Well, what do you say?

1351
01:34:42,307 --> 01:34:44,726
Everything points
to a duckling.

1352
01:34:46,979 --> 01:34:48,730
Help me.

1353
01:34:52,359 --> 01:34:54,486
For heaven's sake...

1354
01:34:54,569 --> 01:34:56,738
help me.

1355
01:34:56,822 --> 01:34:59,074
I can't even sleep.

1356
01:35:15,841 --> 01:35:18,301
It's the duckling!

1357
01:35:18,385 --> 01:35:21,054
[ Music Stops ]
[ Indistinct Chattering ]

1358
01:36:06,600 --> 01:36:09,519
[ Opera ]

1359
01:36:54,106 --> 01:36:56,984
[ Woman Singing Opera In French ]

1360
01:37:07,828 --> 01:37:10,080
[ Opera Continues ]

1361
01:37:43,947 --> 01:37:45,657
Come here!

1362
01:37:47,951 --> 01:37:50,620
- I'm tired.
- Come here.

1363
01:37:56,626 --> 01:37:58,503
Where are we here?

1364
01:37:58,628 --> 01:38:01,506
I might have taken
the wrong way.

1365
01:38:01,548 --> 01:38:04,676
Good boy, sleep.
Dream sweet dreams.

1366
01:38:04,801 --> 01:38:07,179
Maybe it's only a dream!

1367
01:38:07,220 --> 01:38:09,348
We're dreaming, Joshua.

1368
01:38:09,473 --> 01:38:11,975
Tomorrow morning
Mommy will come wake us up...

1369
01:38:12,059 --> 01:38:16,355
and bring us two nice cups
of milk and cookies.

1370
01:38:16,480 --> 01:38:18,565
First, we'll eat.

1371
01:38:18,690 --> 01:38:21,652
Then I'll make love to her
two or three times...

1372
01:38:22,486 --> 01:38:24,029
if I can.

1373
01:38:29,660 --> 01:38:32,579
- [ Music Fades ]
[ Wind Howling ]

1374
01:38:56,937 --> 01:39:01,608
[ Man On P.A. Speaking German ]
[ Shouting ]

1375
01:39:01,733 --> 01:39:04,611
[ Gunfire ]
[ Dogs Barking ]

1376
01:39:13,203 --> 01:39:15,372
Excuse me, Bartolomeo.

1377
01:39:15,414 --> 01:39:19,042
They've called those two officers
20 times. I bet they escaped.

1378
01:39:19,126 --> 01:39:23,422
- Did you understand anything else?
- It's clear enough.

1379
01:39:23,547 --> 01:39:26,216
The war is over.
They're running all over the place.

1380
01:39:26,258 --> 01:39:28,760
Where are those trucks going?

1381
01:39:28,885 --> 01:39:31,638
The important thing is
not to get on those trucks.

1382
01:39:31,763 --> 01:39:33,932
They leave full
and come back empty.

1383
01:39:34,057 --> 01:39:35,934
You know where they're going?

1384
01:39:37,477 --> 01:39:39,771
What about the women?
What's going on?

1385
01:39:39,813 --> 01:39:42,774
Let's get out of this dump
and split up.

1386
01:39:42,816 --> 01:39:44,985
We don't even have
to pack our bags!

1387
01:39:45,110 --> 01:39:47,738
[ Gunfire Continues ]
- I've been hearing
only dogs and machine guns.

1388
01:39:47,779 --> 01:39:51,074
- They want to get rid of everything.
- I'm leaving.

1389
01:39:51,158 --> 01:39:54,661
See you in Viareggio.
We'll start an anvil factory!

1390
01:39:54,786 --> 01:39:56,163
So long, guys.
I'm leaving.

1391
01:39:56,288 --> 01:40:00,125
[ Shouting In German ]
[ Vehicles Departing ]

1392
01:40:13,638 --> 01:40:15,349
Come see.

1393
01:40:15,474 --> 01:40:18,185
Look how mad they are!
Furious!

1394
01:40:19,478 --> 01:40:21,813
You see?
They're looking for you.

1395
01:40:21,938 --> 01:40:24,024
Just for you.
All this is over you!

1396
01:40:24,149 --> 01:40:26,151
You're the last one!
The last one to find!

1397
01:40:26,276 --> 01:40:29,488
They're even looking
under the rocks!

1398
01:40:29,613 --> 01:40:32,366
The game is over tomorrow.
They'll give the award.

1399
01:40:32,491 --> 01:40:35,786
If they don't find you tonight,
it's worth 60 points!

1400
01:40:35,827 --> 01:40:37,663
How many points do we have?

1401
01:40:37,704 --> 01:40:40,791
We've got 940 points.
Plus 60?

1402
01:40:40,874 --> 01:40:43,168
- A thousand!
- First place! We win!

1403
01:40:43,293 --> 01:40:45,712
They're looking
all over for you.

1404
01:40:45,837 --> 01:40:48,173
No mistakes tonight.
This is it!

1405
01:40:48,298 --> 01:40:51,718
- Go hide in that box, quick!
- Schwanz is in there.

1406
01:40:51,843 --> 01:40:53,679
Who?

1407
01:40:53,720 --> 01:40:56,056
The blond boy.

1408
01:40:58,350 --> 01:41:00,852
They got him yesterday.
He was eliminated.

1409
01:41:00,977 --> 01:41:03,730
It's the safest place to hide.
Nobody will look.

1410
01:41:03,855 --> 01:41:06,692
Let's go, quick as lightning.
Come on!

1411
01:41:10,237 --> 01:41:12,155
Inside!

1412
01:41:12,239 --> 01:41:15,200
Take this blanket
in case you get cold.

1413
01:41:15,242 --> 01:41:17,536
I'll be back soon.

1414
01:41:17,577 --> 01:41:21,039
I'll put them on the wrong track.
I think I saw him over there!

1415
01:41:32,050 --> 01:41:34,553
[ Woman Shouting In German ]

1416
01:41:50,569 --> 01:41:53,947
Pop, you scared me to death!

1417
01:41:54,072 --> 01:41:56,116
Give me the blanket.
Are you cold?

1418
01:41:56,241 --> 01:41:58,118
Give me your sweater then.

1419
01:41:58,243 --> 01:42:01,288
I'll throw it on a tree
and put them off-track.

1420
01:42:01,413 --> 01:42:04,374
They're looking all over for you!

1421
01:42:04,458 --> 01:42:07,085
Everybody's yelling,
"Where's Joshua?"

1422
01:42:07,210 --> 01:42:10,881
They're even cursing.
They're really, really mad!

1423
01:42:10,922 --> 01:42:14,259
No one will find you.
Bye, now. I'll be back later.

1424
01:42:15,260 --> 01:42:17,054
Listen...

1425
01:42:17,095 --> 01:42:20,265
if I'm really late coming back...

1426
01:42:20,390 --> 01:42:22,267
don't you move.

1427
01:42:22,309 --> 01:42:25,604
Don't come out.
You're not to come out...

1428
01:42:25,645 --> 01:42:29,149
until it's completely quiet...

1429
01:42:29,274 --> 01:42:31,443
and nobody is in sight,
just to be safe.

1430
01:42:31,568 --> 01:42:32,944
Say it!

1431
01:42:32,986 --> 01:42:36,323
I won't come out
until nobody is around.

1432
01:42:36,448 --> 01:42:38,450
Good boy, stubborn.

1433
01:42:40,952 --> 01:42:42,829
Ciao. Ciao.

1434
01:42:54,132 --> 01:42:57,010
[ Dog Barking ]

1435
01:43:07,437 --> 01:43:08,855
Leave!

1436
01:43:08,980 --> 01:43:11,108
Go away, dog!

1437
01:43:11,149 --> 01:43:13,193
Go, dog!

1438
01:43:13,318 --> 01:43:14,695
Leave.

1439
01:43:27,666 --> 01:43:29,292
Good job, Ferruccio.

1440
01:43:29,334 --> 01:43:31,336
It works.

1441
01:43:37,009 --> 01:43:39,970
[ Woman Shouting ]

1442
01:43:54,860 --> 01:43:58,155
Dora? Is there anyone
called Dora here?

1443
01:43:58,196 --> 01:44:00,073
Dora? Dora?

1444
01:44:36,151 --> 01:44:38,028
Dora?

1445
01:44:38,153 --> 01:44:40,197
Dora, are you here?
It's Guido.

1446
01:44:41,323 --> 01:44:44,534
I know someone is hiding here.
Is there a Dora here?

1447
01:44:44,660 --> 01:44:45,661
[ Woman ]
No.

1448
01:44:54,169 --> 01:44:57,172
Is there a Dora here?
She's Italian. She's my wife.

1449
01:44:57,214 --> 01:45:00,217
Yes, there's a Dora here.

1450
01:45:01,176 --> 01:45:03,095
It's me, Dora!

1451
01:45:04,513 --> 01:45:06,765
It's not her!
Is there another Dora?

1452
01:45:06,848 --> 01:45:09,184
Jump out of the truck
as soon as you can!

1453
01:45:09,226 --> 01:45:11,603
Get off! Jump out!

1454
01:45:11,687 --> 01:45:13,689
[ Shouts ]

1455
01:45:14,940 --> 01:45:17,109
[ Whistle Blowing ]
[ German ]

1456
01:45:49,141 --> 01:45:52,060
[ Man Shouting In German ]

1457
01:45:53,311 --> 01:45:56,231
[ German ]

1458
01:46:04,823 --> 01:46:07,743
[ Yelling In German ]

1459
01:46:09,411 --> 01:46:11,455
[ Dogs Barking ]

1460
01:46:25,177 --> 01:46:28,096
[ Giggling ]

1461
01:46:33,518 --> 01:46:36,438
[ Yelling Continues ]

1462
01:46:55,874 --> 01:47:00,045
[ Bombs Exploding ]

1463
01:47:04,549 --> 01:47:07,511
[ Gunfire ]

1464
01:47:22,859 --> 01:47:25,821
[ Shouting In German ]
[ Vehicles Departing ]

1465
01:48:04,735 --> 01:48:07,696
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

1466
01:50:00,225 --> 01:50:02,477
[ Vehicle Approaching ]

1467
01:50:29,838 --> 01:50:31,840
It's true!

1468
01:50:41,558 --> 01:50:43,352
Hi, boy.

1469
01:50:46,271 --> 01:50:49,441
You all alone?
What's your name?

1470
01:50:51,443 --> 01:50:53,445
You don't understand
what I'm sayin', do ya?

1471
01:50:53,528 --> 01:50:55,572
We'll give you a lift.
Come on!

1472
01:50:55,697 --> 01:50:57,574
Come on.
Get up here.

1473
01:51:02,037 --> 01:51:03,955
[ Man ]
This way. Come on!

1474
01:51:04,039 --> 01:51:05,957
Come on!

1475
01:51:06,041 --> 01:51:08,210
[ Men Shouting ]
- Here ya go.

1476
01:51:08,293 --> 01:51:10,295
Whoop!

1477
01:51:51,795 --> 01:51:53,296
Mommy!

1478
01:51:54,798 --> 01:51:56,758
Stop!

1479
01:51:58,677 --> 01:52:00,679
Mama!

1480
01:52:04,850 --> 01:52:09,104
- This is mystery.
- Mama!

1481
01:52:09,187 --> 01:52:11,898
This is the sacrifiice
my father made.

